@NODE "Mail_3" "Re: Window Patterns"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 25 Mar 1999 00:46:03 +0000
From: "Scott" <scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk>
	<blitz-list@egroups.com>
Subject: Re: Window Patterns
Date: Wed, 24 Mar 1999 22:34:27 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hello James,

On the 23rd March 1999, James L Boyd must have been typing for hours...

[Mammoth code example removed (o;]

Alternatively, you could try this:

Statement WBackFill{win.b,patt.l,col.b}
  ad.l=RastPort(win)
  Poke.l ad+8,&patt
  Poke.b ad+$1d,1
  WBox WLeftOff,WTopOff,InnerWidth+WLeftOff-1,InnerHeight+WTopOff-1,col
  Poke.l ad+8,0
  Poke.b ad+$1d,1
End Statement

FindScreen 0
Window 0,0,0,200,200,$100f,"",1,2
WBackFill{0,$aaaa5555,2} ;Requester Background
MouseWait
End

This will fill the whole inner part of the window with a reqtools type fill.
You can achieve different effects by altering the pattern and colour parameters.
Also, you could modify the statement to fill any area size you want, but for now
it just calculates the inner area of the window (works on normal & gzz windows)

Regards,
Scott

scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk



Damn the prime directive, give the Borg Windows 3.1   -   Lt. Worf




