time
> for games to conform themselves to the user instead of the other way
> around. Such a game could be SO much more interesting (but of course
> would force us programmers to get off our lazy duffs and WORK!).

  Yes, I love that! It's hard work to do though. Games like
Armour-Geddon were awesome because of this!  Another from memory was an
RPG- Lure of the Enchantress- the townsfolk went around and did their
own business, went home, then slept, got up and worked and interacted
with each other etc, so you had to approach them at the right time- ie:
at their shop at daytime, not wake them up in the middle of the night,
or you'd get tossed in the slammer!!
 
