And every console magazine I`ve picked up in the last few months....it
sounds to me like another Japanese roleplaying game...and this time...your
not rescuing fair dragons from foul fire breathing maidens, or hunting for
long forgotten treasure....or time travelling to vanquish evil
empires....your doing what anyone could do every single day of the week in
real life...that`s all my point was....under the thread titled....What`s
Fun??

>> If you can`t tell what sarcasm is....try askin,

>Quite obviosly you missed the point entirely. You have probably never
played a game that gave you the >freedom to do whatever you wanted to, I
mourn your loss... (Or maybe you where being ironically sarcastic ?)


nope...I just make a line up, and attach it at the bottom...it never usually
means anything...just the first thing that pops into my head.....I have
played lots of games....and never found one that gave me the freedom to do
what I want...I even have baldurs gate, might and magic IV....half life,
sin...all the ones that have been mentioned lately...(even gta....which I
don`t rate...and think that it spoils DMA`s fairly good history....if you
look at there other N64 games...like body harvest and the new ones....you`ll
see that they make good games most of the time...ie..playable..even if the
gfx isn`t the best in the world!). Baldurs gate doesn`t give you any
particular amazing freedom..it`s the same as any other decent rpg I`ve
played (in fact...it`s worse than some...how bad is the programming when
they use 5 cd`s....ever heard of bitmap compression???...in fact..I should
sue them for breaking my 16 speed cd rom!)....it has some good points..it
looks good..and is based on ad+d, but I found m+m better in the long
run...but there both games where you have missions to complete...you can
choose which order to do some of them in, and you get random treasure...but
other than that...the game the same if you play it again, as the missions
are fixed). The day I play a good game, where the missions are generated as
you play, and the characters interact properly (ie, in might and magic...a
shop opens from say, 6am-6pm...so why, when I can destory a sky full of
dragons...can I not bust in and steal everything from a small wooden shack
at night???) and the people of the village do not just randomly move
about...then I will be happy ;).


How much wood, could a woodchuck chuck, if a woodchuck could chuck wood??

Dave





