  I think this is a GREAT idea!

  I would like to see it eventually cover all of the aspects of game
programming so that even beginners can benifit from it, but my own
personal preferances for starters would be such things as are likely
to expand the knowledge of those who already know the basics.

  I would like to suggest such things as isometric maps, 3D techniques,
artificial intelligence routines, pathfinding, improving displays
(including for graphics boards), optimising graphics handling,
optimising code in general, color palette optimizing, modular graphics,
animation techniques, object priority handling and useful coding tricks.

