From: "S.J.CROY" <ap6013@qmw.ac.uk>
Organization: University of London (QMW)
Date: Mon, 8 Mar 1999 11:39:58 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Re: Web Page and Question


Hello Oliver

> Is there anyway i can get a list of all the open screen so that i can send
> a window to the screen selected by the user.

I`ve been working on a smilar problem myself.  I don`t have access 
to the code off hand but here is a general run through.

1) Open intuition library
2) Set up a loop
3) increase counter to the next screen
4) until (no next screen or counter=screen wanted)
5) close library

Here comes the code
(needs amigalibs.res present)


*Intuition. IntuitionBase = OpenLibrary_ ("intuition.library",37)

if *Intuition
	*Scr.Screen = *Intuition\FirstScreen
	finished=false


	lock.l= LockIBase_ (0)   ;Make sure intuition doesn`t 	
					;modify anything

	repeat
		if *Scr\NextScreen
			*Scr=*Scr\NextScreen
		else
			finished=false
		endif		

	until finished=true


	UnlockIBase_ ( lock )

	closelibrary_ (*Intuition)

endif


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_56" "WCls and Sliders"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 6 Mar 1999 02:12:11 +0000
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Fri, 05 Mar 1999 21:09:04 +0500
Subject: WCls and Sliders

Could someone tell me how to make it so a gadget (specifically a slider)
doesn't disappear when I use the WCls command? I thought of putting a
borderless window on the bottom of the window I'm clearing, but I want to be
able to drag both windows around. Can I somehow attach the two windows?
-- 
-If the doors of perception were cleansed everything would appear to man as it
truly is, infinite.-



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_57" "Re: WCls and Sliders"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 6 Mar 1999 14:22:38 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 05 Mar 1999 21:34:05 -0500
Subject: Re: WCls and Sliders

Hi Jake

On 05-Mar-99, Jake Frederick wrote:
> Could someone tell me how to make it so a gadget (specifically a slider)
> doesn't disappear when I use the WCls command?

No, WCLS erases the whole window.  Why not use WBox instead, to only clear
the part above the slider?

Or you could do a "Redraw" right after WCLS to put the gadget back... 

>I thought of putting a
> borderless window on the bottom of the window I'm clearing, but I want to
> be able to drag both windows around. Can I somehow attach the two
windows?

I think you'd have to do this manually, by watching  for the main window
being moved, then move the other one to match.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_58" "WCls and Sliders"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 16:54:09 +0000
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Jake Frederick
Subject: WCls and Sliders
Date: 07 Mar 1999 15:42:39
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 5 Mar 99 Jake Frederick wrote about 'WCls and Sliders'.

 JF> Could someone tell me how to make it so a gadget (specifically a
 JF> slider) doesn't disappear when I use the WCls command?

You can't, all the gadgets imagery will be overwritten, even though the gad=
gets
still exist. The easiest way, if you REALLY have to WCls is to issue a
GT_RefreshWindow_ Peek.l(Addr Window(x),0 where 'x' is the number of your
window. This will tell Gadtools to refresh all the gadgets in the window.

Simon Archer



