Well it's about as much as a minidisc player (portable) and the sound
quality
is much better in the minidisc. And you can have multiple dsics for your
minidisc
to a very low price. A new memoy cartride for the MP-Man (mp3 player is
called
that) costs a fortune. An in all the tests of MP-Man's Vs. Minidiscs the
minidiscs
has always won, and has gotten a much higher mark when it comes to sound
quality. Now about mp3. Use em on your Minidisc then. You just need a RCA to
3.5mm cable and you can record anything you want. So hock it up to the sound
output on your miggy and start recoding em illegal tunes. I've done this
loads
of time and never had ne probs..

NOW Lets get back ontopic...Just wanted to save you guys from wasting alot
of money on crap when ya can get something really good for the same price.

 BYe!




