On 27-Mar-99, Rick Hodger flashed:

>> Yes, as opposed to in real life where they would just shit themselves and
>> die.

>Yeah, seeing as most standard hand-grenades come with a three second fuse
>which starts the instant the fly-handle comes off.  You'd get just enough
>time to see it come bouncing across the floor towards you before it takes
>your legs orf....oops, I think I've said too much...


  Not that it matters in this discussion much but the hand grenades I used
had an 8 second fuze.  In the most of the situations we were in, a 3 second
fuze would have been more dangerous to us than the enemy.  Allthough if
you were outside of a hardened bunker in a very exposed condition a 3
second fuze might be nice, I don't know as I was never in that particular
situation.  You would want to be VERY sure not to muff it by slipping a
little, or fumbling it, or finding you didn't have as good a place to get
rid of it as you thought a few seconds earlier.  All of these things are
VERY likely to happen in a firefight.  There were times when I actually was
thankful for my training.



Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)



