Le 01-Mars-99, Curt Esser a =E9crit:

>Well, the thing is that the tokens are 2 bytes, but the first must alway=
s
>be >127 (I suppose so Blitz can tell the difference between a token and =
plain
>text).  But somehow Blitz can get a library number (1-255) and a command=

>number (1-255) from this...

Hi Curt,

yesterday I tried to understand tokens checking them in a bb2 source and =
their
lib and command numbers. Library number goes from 1 (0 ?) to 255 (8 bits)=
 but
command number goes from 0 to 127 (7 bits, this explains certainly your
problem with Mildred lib).

Tokens are 16 bits long :
 lib number cmd number
 /       \/     \
1xxxxxxx xxxxxxxx      (x is 0 or 1 :-)
^ =

bit 7 of the first byte : Blitz understand it's a token.

I looked your program, and apparently you seemed to make that. But I don'=
t
know why your examples don't work with lib 10 and 73. Are you sure 11 and=
 13
libs aren't 10 and 12 (BDGfxLib and another) ?

Maybe you solved your  problem today ? If you need any help ...

Cheers,

                  Mathias



