Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Loki.

On 27-Feb-99, Loki wrote:

> Intuition codeing is SLOW!.. how do you double buffer an ituition scree=
n?

No, intuition coding is fast. I have yet to see any AGA stuff that compea=
ts with a PIV. There are many ways. One is using showbitmap, to attach an=
other bitmap to the screen, another is creating a double height screen, a=
nd switching between the top half, and the bottom half. (This is what Pau=
l Bukey does [or at least used to do], how do I know ? I have a screen pr=
omoter that forces autoscroll, and it wreaks havoc on foundation :o>)

> This was a demo style program I was working on, and required all the
> speed it could grab!

Well, so now you have a program that is very fast, instead no-one can use=
 it.... Hrmm...


Regards
