@NODE "Mail_133" "Re: This is getting annoying!! :(( (MEM LEAK, BAD CODING!)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 4 Mar 1999 20:40:38 +0000
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 4 Mar 1999 20:39:17 +0000
Date: Thu, 04 Mar 1999 13:35:35 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: This is getting annoying!! :(( (MEM LEAK, BAD CODING!)
Encoding: 7bit

Toby Zuijdveld wrote:
> PB>> another is creating a double height screen, and switching between
> PB>> the top half, and the bottom half. (This is what Paul Bukey does
> PB>> [or at least used to do], how do I know ? I have a screen promoter
> PB>> that forces autoscroll, and it wreaks havoc on foundation :o>)
> 
> PB> I don`t use this any more. It was and still is a popular method
> PB> of double buffering on graphics cards. I now discovered that
> PB> allocating a bitmap and cludging a rastport to point to it is
> PB> a good way to do hidden rendering on graphics cards. I also realized
> 
> HOW DO YOU DO THAT?!?
> 
> Please tell me, I'll be your best friend =]

try something like this...

DEFTYPE .RastPort rp                       ; make a rastport structure
DEFTYPE .BitMap *bmp                       ; make a bitmap pointer
InitRastPort_ &rp                          ; create your rastport
*bmp=AllocBitMap_(160,160,8,#BMF_CLEAR,0)  ; create your bitmap
rp\_BitMap=*bmp                            ; point rastport to bitmap

render_here.l=&rp

Now you can use render_here.l for your rastport rendering such
as WritePixelArray8_ etc.

I hope all that works, I just copied it from a bit of old example
code I used durring the testing stages.

Cheers,

Paul

-- 
< Paul Burkey http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk >



