Curt,

> Well, I don't have Mini-Mildred (as I understand it is just a duplicate of
> some of the Mildred commands from the big library.)

Yep, just the c2p stuff.
 
> > Because you DON'T NEED to use these simultaneusly.
> 
> Yes - but how does the Blitz compiler make these commands work then? 
> Because if it is reading the numbers the same as I am, then the Mildred
> commands >127 are telling it to use a library that does not exist  (or the
> wrong library, if I did have #16) - or does the MakeDefLibs automatically
> split Mildred into 2 parts using Library #16 for the second part?
> 
> Because surely the whole Mildred library DOES work...
> 
> But, then why are the system librarys split into 2 parts...

Interesting questions Curt. Mildred is one lib numbered 15. When I had
to modify the makedeflibs it seemed to me that all it did was allocate
enough space in the deflibs file to store the whole object file + 4
bytes, and those 4 bytes are used to tell it how many bytes are in the
object file. I don't know what happens after that, or why other libs
are split into two parts. Maybe it's just to make things friendlier or
something.


-- 
Paul.

