 ([62.136.52.3] helo=all-hail.freeserve.co.uk ident=James L Boyd)
	by mail10.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.12 #1)
	id 10Jc8L-00041B-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 11:54:13 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 07 Mar 1999 11:45:41 +0000
Subject: Re: Tasks and Processes

Brucey churned out *this* drivel :

> And, if you want to change the Priority, use -
> 
>        psetting.w = SetTaskPri_(FindTask_(0),num)
> 
> where - psetting now contains the NEW Priority level,
>        num is the value you want to set.

Not quite right ;)

You should dod a Forbid_/Permit_ around it (can't remember why...)
and the value returned is the /old/ priority of the program...

-----------------------------------------

Function.w SetPriority{newpriority.w}

  If newpriority<-127 OR newpriority>127 Then Function Return 0

  Forbid_                     ;lock system to check for task

  *task.l=FindTask_(*crap.l)  ;*crap.l is only a NULL-Pointer
                              ;this way the task of the program itself
                              ;is returned

; set the new priority:
  oldpriority.w=SetTaskPri_(*task,newpriority.w)

  Permit_                     ;and return the system

Function Return oldpriority.w

End Function 

----------------------------------- 
See ya,
-- 
