Executables are always launched as their DOS names....

 L> to make sure the taskname will be exactly what you want it to be,
 L> and not something different if the user has renamed the file?

...but you can use CreateNewProc to create a new process of the name you=
 want.
There would be no way to change the name of this process, but it does invlo=
ve
a lot of extra work and overhead.

