@NODE "Mail_178" "Subject set, as ezmlm doesnt accept empty subject fields :-)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 24 Mar 1999 00:36:37 +0000
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: amorel
Subject: Subject set, as ezmlm doesnt accept empty subject fields :-)
Date: 24 Mar 1999 00:29:20
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 23 Mar 99 amorel wrote about 'Subject set, as ezmlm doesnt accept empty=
 subject fields :-)'.

 a> What code do you need to put in to be able to use your prog with
 a> version?
 a> I do this:

You don't need to faff about like that, here:

v$ =3D "$VER: MyCrapProg V1.1 (23/3/99)"

That'll work

