@NODE "Mail_190" "SpriteColors."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 24 Mar 1999 17:41:56 +0000
From: Jon Nilsson <sorex@2.sbbs.se>
Date: Thu, 18 Mar 1999 03:08:27 +0100
Subject: SpriteColors.

Hello I've got a little problem. I am showing two sprites in BLITZ
mode but i can't seem to get the colors right. A matter of fact I
doens't seem to be able to change them at all.
The sprites are taken from 4 color shapes.
The Display library is used to setup the display.

So my question is how do you set up the colors in sprites and how
do you alter them. I know they use the colors 17-31 but it doesn't
seem to make any difference if I change them..

Thanks in advance



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_191" "Re: SpriteColors."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 25 Mar 1999 05:03:27 +0000
From: Terry & Tom Stone <tjstone@wkpowerlink.com>
Date: Wed, 02 Sep 1992 13:55:43 +0500
Organization: WKPowerlink
Subject: Re: SpriteColors.
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello,

Keep in mind that 2 bit plane sprites (actually 3 colours and transparent=
)
get their colours from colour registers 17-31; however, depending on the =

sprite channel you use you will be using different colour registers (as s=
tated in the manual):

   sprite channel    colours
      0,1            17-19
      2,3            21-23
      4,5            25-27
      6,7            29-31

So if you want a sprite to use say colours blue/green/purple and
sprite channel 2 or 3, your 32 colour palette MUST have these colors
in colour registers 21-23.

I hope this helps.

Thanks

Tom

On 02-Sep-92, Jon Nilsson wrote:
>Hello I've got a little problem. I am showing two sprites in BLITZ
>mode but i can't seem to get the colors right. A matter of fact I
>doens't seem to be able to change them at all.
>The sprites are taken from 4 color shapes.
>The Display library is used to setup the display.

>So my question is how do you set up the colors in sprites and how
>do you alter them. I know they use the colors 17-31 but it doesn't
>seem to make any difference if I change them..

>Thanks in advance




