@NODE "Mail_207" "Re: Shapies :)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 5 Mar 1999 22:01:08 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 05 Mar 1999 15:34:27 -0500
Subject: Re: Shapies :)

Hi Loki

On 05-Mar-99, Loki wrote:
> Hello,
> 
>  Anyone know how to check if a shape has been initialized?

Peek.l Addr(Shape (whatever)) will tell if a shape is there.

But only if you have not used and free'd this shape before.

Try this way  (assuming you want to use shapes # 1 and 2, and they were used
before)

Free Shape 1   
Free Shape 2
Poke.l Addr Shape(1),0
Poke.l Addr Shape(2),0

IconToShape(1,2)

If Peek.l (Addr Shape(2))
  ;yes, there is a second image
Else
  ;no, only the first image should be used
EndIf
> 
> Reason I ask is cos, IconToShape(Shape#,Shape#) apprears to `free' the
> second shape with Compliment and BackFill Images :( And I keep getting
> `unitialised shape' errors with WBlit all the time :(

Because a Compliment or Backfill icon has only 1 image...

-- 
