@NODE "Mail_214" "SetPatch, 3.1 and Blitz"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 29 Mar 1999 21:21:53 +0100
Date: Mon, 29 Mar 1999 21:26:48 +0100
From: BaH <brucey@thenet.co.uk>
Subject: SetPatch, 3.1 and Blitz

It was with some anticipation that I opened the AMIGA OS box from Power
Computing last week and found a couple of ROMS, disks and manuals.
In went the ROMS.
I booted up, and everything seemed fine.
Then I thought I should install the drivers.  Of course my eagerness came
before much sense and I didn't back up ALL my libs/c/s stuff.
Of course, now I can't get setpatch to work, AT ALL, with my 1260 board.
I downloaded the newest one from Amiga and that don't work either. I just
get a hang then reset.  Anyone have an 060 with Setpatch.  Any other
versions would be appreciated.  The computer does boot with 060 disabled,
but that really defeats the purpose.

And to keep a little bit on topic...
I vaguely remember someone was using a 'different' mod player/library in
blitz for playing the likes of soundtracker/protracker mods.  I think it
might have been Mr Burkey, though I may be wrong.  What is it, and where
might I find it ?

One last thing.  How does Powerpacker on Max compression rate to the
'other' packers ppl seem to be using ??   My chunky bitmaps (320x256)
average around 15k powerpacked (from 80k).
(except at the moment I can't use Mildred as I have no AGA..........)

On with the GUI's......


regards

Brucey

          ( BaH )
         O
        o         PowerMac 6500/250 64mb 10gigHD ZIP100 Jaz2
 ____^_o          Amiga 1260T/50 18mb 4.65gigHD's ZIP100 CD
(    )o\
(____)            brucey@thenet.co.uk
/\ /\
The Sheep has Spoken



