Do you mean the EML library?  It is found in Aminet/dev/basic.  It seems to
work much better than the CIAtracker library for me.
> 
> One last thing.  How does Powerpacker on Max compression rate to the
> 'other' packers ppl seem to be using ??   My chunky bitmaps (320x256)
> average around 15k powerpacked (from 80k).
> (except at the moment I can't use Mildred as I have no AGA..........)

Powerpacker does almost as well as StoneCracker.  But StoneCracker has the
added advantage of direct unpacking support in Blitz...

