>> Certainly the compiler would be nice (So we could
>> finally have that CLI compiler that everyone is talking about :o>)=
=20

>But even if the compiler can't be released, you could still make a C=
LI
>compiler from the SuperTed source, since SuperTed is, in effect, the=
 "front
>end", or "link" to the compiler.  And really all you need to know is=
 how to
>link to the compiler, right?

Hi Curt,

In essence, you'd be right. What happens with Blitz2.1 is this :

Blitz loads
Blitz then LoadSeg()s SuperTED
Blitz then calls various internal SuperTED functions, giving it point=
ers
to various Blitz compiler calls.
SuperTED code is then executed.

I'll have to refresh my memory regarding the state of the various
source codes (ISTR the most recent version allows you to compile/run =
and
edit other source codes at the same time, but I think that was hideou=
sly
unstable!)

Steve.




