>   A little word of advice to every programer.  NEVER relenquish the rights
> to your creations unless it is the only way to make the profits worth your
> while.  

Another thing to do is to copy your source code to floppy, then mail
it to yourself, recorded delivery, in a sealed padded bag.   Then
leave it somewhere safe (solicitor or bank or parent's / children's
house etc.) unopened.    That way there is irrefutable evidence that
you created the source code on or before the date of mailing.

Not a hard thing to do, but can settle a lot of disputes.

Cheers

