@NODE "Mail_295" "Re: Pic exec"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 22 Mar 1999 11:11:19 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Mar 1999 05:05:51 -0500
Subject: Re: Pic exec

Hi Nick,

I hope you're still around  ;)   We're usually pretty friendly  -  honest 

On 21-Mar-99, nickpatts wrote:
> Yes this is what i mean
> 
>> 2) A program that can gerate its own executable with information in
>> with out help of blitz.  In other words a stand alone program.

OK, if I understand right, you want to make something that people can use to
create their own "Self-viewing" pictures, right?

I think what you would need is 2 programs:

One that would decode an IncBin'd picture file that was attached to the very
end of itself, read it's info, and open an appropriate sceen to show it,
etc.

Then a second program that would get the picture file name to be attached
and
allocate a block of memory big enough to hold the "viewing" program and the
picture file.

Now it would load the viewer exec into this block, and the picture file
directly behind it.  Then save off the whole thing as the "Self Viewing
Picture"...

You might run into a problem creating the viewer exec without actually
having a picture attached to it.  Maybe you would need to attach a
"throw-away" one just to get it working, and then remove it later with a
hex editor.

Oh, and don't be surprised when this all crashes the first time (or twelve)
-
you'll probably have to do some playing around to get all the memory offsets
exactly right...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
