@NODE "Mail_298" "SV: Passing Information!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 1 Mar 1999 19:27:51 +0000
 Mon, 1 Mar 1999 20:26:18 +0100 (CET)
 Mon, 1 Mar 1999 20:26:10 +0100 (CET)
From: "Andreas HÕkansson" <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Subject: SV: Passing Information!
Date: Mon, 1 Mar 1999 20:25:01 +0100


>   Anyone know a way to pass information between 2 programs?
>IE, To pass a string from one task to another seemlessly.


Yeah, you would do it like this. Lets say you want to share a variabel
thats called text$ what you would do it to get the adress of text$ and
save itin a temp file in ram (perhaps in t). the other program would then
open the file and read in the adress and point his text$ variable to
that adress. Now when since the text$ variable points to the same
memory adress, changin it in one of the programs would mean it
affects the contents of text$ in the other program as well.

Also adding some simple "error" checking, wich lets you start any
of the programs first and still being able to share a variable, isnt
a dum idea. You would do something like this

If exist(ram:test)
  <open the file>
  <read the adress>
  <point text$ to that adress>
  <close file>
else
  <get the adress of text$>
  <open a file called test in ram>
  <save the adress>
  <close file>
endif

put this in both programs and it will work like a charm =) If you dont
know hw to get the adres sof a variable and save it, or point a variable
to an adress then let me know and I'll send you a small example

Bye!








@ENDNODE
