@NODE "Mail_306" "Re: Passing Information!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 4 Mar 1999 18:50:07 +0000
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 4 Mar 1999 18:48:07 +0000
From: Chris Deeney <chris@addnet.demon.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 04 Mar 1999 18:46:55 +0000
Organization: personal
Subject: Re: Passing Information!

Heyz Loki

On 01-Mar-99, Loki wrote:
> Hello dewdz,
> 
>   Anyone know a way to pass information between 2 programs?
> IE, To pass a string from one task to another seemlessly.
> 
> Any ideas?
> 
> Thanks.
> Cya!

I used a method that talks directly with the other proggy :)

First proggy:

wbstartup
a.b=100

execute_ "proggy2 "+&a.b

repeat
nprint "watch how 'a' changes value!?"
nprint a.b
vwait
until joyb(0)=3
end

second proggy:

wbstartup
p$=par$(0) ; get proggy parameters

addy.l=var(p$)

for n=0 to 127
poke.b addy.l,n
vwait 5
next

end
-- 
                                    Chris "PrinceD" Deeney
