Hi Anton

>   Can it be done to a chunky bitmap in fast?

 I don't follow your question but ATM whats happening is this:

1) Request character bitmap from bullet.library (one plane planar bitmap, =
might 
be in fast mem, might be in chip mem)
2) Copy the bitmap to a temporary bitmap in chip mem
3) Use BltTemplate_ to blit the character to a rastport. BltTemplate_ uses=
 the 
rastport settings, i.e. font colour, drawmode, etc.

 I want something that lets me skip step 2, but steps 3 should work as it =
does 
with BltTemplate_. It was just if anyone had something lying around.

 Since this stuff is just for standard intuition things just now, I was ho=
ping 
that the graphics.library drawing routines would take of GFX cards by 
themselves. Could someone test that this works please 
(http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn/files/outline.lha)?


