@NODE "Mail_316" "Re: Optimization and exe size (again, sorry!)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 17 Mar 1999 02:48:27 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Mar 1999 20:39:47 -0500
Subject: Re: Optimization and exe size (again, sorry!)

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1748394248.1

Hi John

On 16-Mar-99, John Mason wrote:
> Hi all,
>  
>  A while ago some people were talking about optimizing their Blitz code
> and using OS functions to reduce their exe's size.  ISTR someone making
an
> AmigaGuide document

It's attached - I don't remember where I found it.

> or a program that suggested ways to do this 

On my web site (not on Aminet yet) you'll find a program "Investigator"
that
will read through your source code and tell you which commands you used,
how many times each, and what library they are from.  So if you see that
you only used one or two commands from a certain library, you can try to
find another way, maybe using OS commands instead, or replacing them with
commands from other libraries.

There are also some examples of ways to use OS commands on my site, and many
more on the other sites listed there.

And look in Aminet/dev/basic for James Boyd's  StatsFuncts file, which has
many OS routines in it.

And get Fred's NCS libraries, which are replacements for many Blitz
commands, and produce much smaller execs.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748394248.1
