From: "Andreas HÕkansson" <andy@bjuv.mail.telia.com>
Subject: New editor
Date: Fri, 12 Mar 1999 20:19:04 +0100


Well people. I have some nice info to share with you. There is already a
new
editor being written, by me. It will have all of the things we miss in
supetTed. To
mention some:

- Window based, like goldED. So you can have multiple source codes open
   next to eachother at the same time.
- "Color code", meaing you can set the colors that ie. statement/functions,
  comments, strings etc sould be displayed in.
- Library statistics, meaning you can get a listing of which libaries is
being
  used in your code, which commands from them, and how many times
  each command is being used. This is valuable information when it comes
  to reducing the size of your exe file(s).
- Statement/function folding.
- Configurable GUI (like goldED)
- Perhaps a Compile option, if Steve will release the code to show how to
  use the compiler from within your program(s) etc.
- Project system, meaing you can save/load a entire project (all files that
it
  uses) at a time.
- Project Investigator - Shows what files being used  in your project.
- Being able to load and save tokenized souce code, as well as ascii files
- And more

Now much of this is actually already done, in seperat test programs. I can
already read all the commands from libs as well as identifying lib types
etc,
load an ascii file into an editor window, etc.

What needs to be done is mainly to load/save tokenized files, compiling from
the editor (come on Steve...spill be beans on this one atleast), making the
GUI
configurable as well as making the text windows editable, meaning adding a
cursor
and being able to edit the contents.

This souldnt be hard to implement, how ever working with tokenized source
will
be added later (I know Curt Esser is working on this problem). So what do
you
guys think? Is it work finishing this program for everyone to use for FREE?

If ya guyes like this, then I will continue work and finish it asap.

  bye!






@ENDNODE
