Actually, GoldED does tokenise source (including commands from Blitz
libraries, numbers, constants, strings and comments), and does create
label lists.  I have the files to do that sitting on my HD :)  It can
also do procedure folding, and it is possible to have a plugin that will
show the syntax for a command when the cursor is moved over the command
name.

