@NODE "Mail_342" "My Tuppence Worth Again"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 13 Mar 1999 15:24:09 +0000
From: "Jes" <jes@cosmothecat.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: My Tuppence Worth Again
Date: Sat, 13 Mar 1999 15:19:29 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

To all,

    Hi.  This is my first posting to the list - hope I don't upset anyone
with the following comments.

    Firstly, alas, I use a PC for all my on-line stuff as I don't have the
amiga stuff.  Still, it does the job admirably......most of the time.

    Secondly, all this chat about the new list going on.  Well, it's not
really about programming is it?  I mean, ok, this is meant to be a forum for
blitz related stuff but mainly it seems to be bickering and nonsense.
Sorry.

    Thirdly, please keep reading :-)

    Almost finally, I have been programming for a long time now in loads of
languages, having cut my teeth in CBM 64 BASIC and worked through 6502,
Pascal, DBase, Cobol, Prolog, C, etc ad nauseum, but have to say that Blitz
is certainly my favourite language to program in, mainly because it's Miggy
specific.  But still....there is a LOT of stuff going on with this list that
leaves me scrabbling in the dust.
    Some of you guys( and girls Liz ;-) ) obviously know an awful lot about
the miggy and about blitz, and you stride off into the distance leaving some
of us behind, not knowing what the Hell is going on.
    My point - not sure, really, but having two lists suggests that you
could perhaps have a beginners list( with Ye Great Gurus giving advice from
on high ) and also an advanced user list which we mere mortals can read and
hope to aspire to.  It's only a suggestion, but I'd be intrerested to see
what people think.

    Finally, Long live the Amiga and all that - maybe one day I'll be able
to afford to put some stuff into the tower I bought and hopefully it won't
be bankrupt stock.  Keep going folks - before getting online these lists
were my first port of call on the AF coverdisc each month - give yourselves
a pat on the back( or whatever part of your anatomy you like ) as you have
helped keep at least one person interested.

    Long Livers and Pisspoor ! or something that like that anyway,


                                            Jes


    Amiga Setup :    1200 Tower, 640meg HD, 8 meg ram expansion( seems like
I'm the poor kid on the block )

    Current Projects :    about 3 million unfinished games, utilities and
stuff.  You know how it



@ENDNODE
