	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_0004_01BE6D5E.F201A4E0"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

------=_NextPart_000_0004_01BE6D5E.F201A4E0
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: quoted-printable

To all,

    Hi.  This is my first posting to the list - hope I don't upset =
anyone with the following comments.

    Firstly, alas, I use a PC for all my on-line stuff as I don't have =
the amiga stuff.  Still, it does the job admirably......most of the =
time.

    Secondly, all this chat about the new list going on.  Well, it's not =
really about programming is it?  I mean, ok, this is meant to be a forum =
for blitz related stuff but mainly it seems to be bickering and =
nonsense.  Sorry.

    Thirdly, please keep reading :-)

    Almost finally, I have been programming for a long time now in loads =
of languages, having cut my teeth in CBM 64 BASIC and worked through =
6502, Pascal, DBase, Cobol, Prolog, C, etc ad nauseum, but have to say =
that Blitz is certainly my favourite language to program in, mainly =
because it's Miggy specific.  But still....there is a LOT of stuff going =
on with this list that leaves me scrabbling in the dust.
    Some of you guys( and girls Liz ;-) ) obviously know an awful lot =
about the miggy and about blitz, and you stride off into the distance =
leaving some of us behind, not knowing what the Hell is going on.
    My point - not sure, really, but having two lists suggests that you =
could perhaps have a beginners list( with Ye Great Gurus giving advice =
from on high ) and also an advanced user list which we mere mortals can =
read and hope to aspire to.  It's only a suggestion, but I'd be =
intrerested to see what people think.

    Finally, Long live the Amiga and all that - maybe one day I'll be =
able to afford to put some stuff into the tower I bought and hopefully =
it won't be bankrupt stock.  Keep going folks - before getting online =
these lists were my first port of call on the AF coverdisc each month - =
give yourselves a pat on the back( or whatever part of your anatomy you =
like ) as you have helped keep at least one person interested.

    Long Livers and Pisspoor ! or something that like that anyway,


                                            Jes
                                                   =20

    Amiga Setup :    1200 Tower, 640meg HD, 8 meg ram expansion( seems =
like I'm the poor kid on the block )

    Current Projects :    about 3 million unfinished games, utilities =
and stuff.  You know how it is.

