the minidiscs
>  > has always won, and has gotten a much higher mark when it comes to
sound
>  > quality. Now about mp3. Use em on your Minidisc then. You just need =
a
RCA to
>  > 3.5mm cable and you can record anything you want. So hock it up to t=
he
sound
>  > output on your miggy and start recoding em illegal tunes. I've done
this
>  > loads of time and never had ne probs..
>  =

>  Ah, well actually high quality MPEG layer 3 files are better than
MiniDisc quality. Offcourse wheter the decompession and sound hardware in=

the MP-man as you call it is any good is another matter all together. But=

theoetically, it could be done, and you wouldn't have any "bumps" in soun=
d
when doing stuff (like running, fighting, having sex) and it could easily=
 be
built to be watertight down to incedible depths (so you could listen to
music while SCUBA diving :o>) and ofcourse, since it has no moving parts =
it
can work in all climates and conditions. Very handy actually. IMHO.

Well Minidiscs and MP3 compressions are totaly different, because Minidis=
c
isn't "lossy" (it cuts the higher and lower sounds which people can't hea=
r)
and thus it's much better quality than MP3.

The early Minidiscs were grap due to the fact that people didn't know how=

to use it (same thing with DVD), but now they are as good as CDs.
And MP3 is not, because of it's nature. Even if you would use totaly
unsensible bitratios it still is lossy. Of course using Walkman style
things you really can't tell the difference.
But it's always nice to have new posibilities.
The new coming MP3 CD player will have some hevy usage. Don't need to lis=
ten
same songs over and over again while bikeing. :)

