@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_361" "Re: Mouse Coordinates"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 5 Mar 1999 18:34:28 +0000
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 5 Mar 1999 18:33:25 +0000
Date: Fri, 05 Mar 1999 16:04:26 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Mouse Coordinates
Encoding: 7bit

Jake Frederick wrote:
> 
> How can I find the mouse coordinates in Amiga mode?

SMouseX and SMouseY are mouse coordinates relative to the screen.
EMouseX and EMouseY are mouse coordinates relative to the window
at the time of the most recent mouse intuition Event. This second
method is the best!

Cheers,

Paul

-- 
< Paul Burkey http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk >



@ENDNODE
