From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 08 Mar 1999 17:09:45 +0000
Subject: Re: Mouse Coordinates

Jake Frederick churned out *this* drivel :

> How can I find the mouse coordinates in Amiga mode?

Assuming you have your window/screen already open :

-------------------------------------------------------
Blitz commands : 

Screen offsets -
SmouseX,SMouseY

Window offsets -
WmouseX,WMouseY

Position in window at most recent IDCMP event -
EMouseX,EMouseY

-------------------------------------------------------

OS Commands :

Screen offsets -

*scr.Screen=Peek.l(Addr Screen(0)) ; replace 0 with number of open screen

x.w=*scr\_MouseX
y.w=*scr\_MouseY

Window offsets -

*win.Window=Peek.l(Addr Window (0)) ; replace 0 with number of open window

x.w=*win\_MouseX
y.w=*win\_MouseY

-------------------------------------------------------

See ya,
-- 
