Hello d.boaz@virgin.net.

On 01-Mar-99, d.boaz@virgin.net wrote:

>     Anyone one have any info on playing Tracker Mods?

Erm, no. Not right here.

>     I`m not talking about using one of the Blitz libs
>     I want to know how to decode and play it with my
>     own code. I once found a web-page about the file
>     format but there seemed to be about 20+ different
>     types of format, is there a main or normal format,
>     or would I need to support them all really?

Well, obviously you would only need to support the one you use. And there=
 are at least 20 different format, actually more than 60.

They include :

SoundTracker (old)
SoundTracker
SoundFX
ProTracker
NoiseTracker
StarTracker

These ae some of the most commonly used, the formats are also very simila=
r and easy to adapt to play each others modules. If you want the replayer=
 code it is usually distibuted along with the program, try looking on Ami=
net or something. It is usually witten in Assembly, with no or little doc=
umentation, so it's probably best to just use the EML (or whatever it's c=
alled) for blitz.


Regards
