@NODE "Mail_376" "Re: Mildred reEEemap!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 31 Mar 1999 11:58:01 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 31 Mar 99 11:44:23 +0000
Subject: Re: Mildred reEEemap!
Encoding: 7bit

> just a thought right, why doesn't someone make a kewl remap table generator
> for mildred, with a nice gui and stuff, that would be really cool :)
> 
> By the way Paul, Mildred is soooooo good :))


Well, it's an idea I thought of a while ago..to actually put in some
tokens to generate the tables. But then you run into the fact that
there are so many possible tables to generate. I suppose you could
have a program that gave you some basic tables like different levels
of transparency, add a tint, add and subtract, negative, etc.. could
be useful I suppose. Another main reason I haven't put this stuff into
tokens is because it really is a pretty dam slow process so isn't ever
likely to be done realtime. Even a simple table for MSimpleReMapMode
takes a good few seconds to compute.

BTW I just added MAddMode, a new blit mode that affects the scrolls,
blits, particles and drawing instructions, and basically adds the
source colour to the destination colour. Makes it faster to do simple
stuff like shade bobs and stuff, and to emulate colour cycling. In
fact, maybe you noticed, but I am trying to provide software methods
of doing most things that you used to be able to do with a custom
copperlist. MAddMode will be in the next release, anyway.

-- 
Paul.

