Erm, actually base64 "encoding" is much better than other (UU/XX) encodin=
g algoythms, it's all because some ISP only allows "old" 7bit mails (ASCI=
I7) which means that every 7 bytes are changed to 8 ASCII7 charecters (56=
bits) and then padded with one bit, this gives an entire text with no byt=
e values larger than 127, which can then be sent to any ISP or BBS or wha=
tever.

Now once all ISP/BSS's in the wold except 8bit encoding, there will be no=
 need to "process" the executable anymore, and your mail size won't gow b=
ecause of attachments. (Or anything else)


Regards
-- =

