@NODE "Mail_379" "Memory Locations"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 14 Mar 1999 20:51:40 +0000
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.idps.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 14 Mar 1999 19:35:41 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Memory Locations

Hi,
   How do you find the memory location of a file which has been IncBin 'd
into code? 

My code looks like this::

 #INCDIR# "Work:Games/AB_Saga/"
 #IncBin# "title.iff"
 #IncBin# "menu.iff"
 #IncBin# "selector.bsh"
 #IncBin# "music.mod"

 #DecodeModule# 1,<ADDRESS>
 #PlayModule# 1
 #MouseWait#
# End#

 I don't know what <ADDRESS> is for the "music.mod" file, so the program
reports an error! Help.

BTW, in case u were wondering, AB_Saga is Alien Breed Saga. I have collected
every Alien Breed game, from the original all the way up to TKG, so I have
put it one box, and this is going to be a HD loader menu for some of them,
like the one u get with Lotus Trilogy.

Cheers in advance.
Cya!
