Hi Mikkel

On 16-Mar-99, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:
> Hello Gareth.
> =

> On 14-Mar-99, Gareth Griffiths wrote:
>> Hi,
>>   How do you find the memory location of a file which has been IncBin =
'd
>> into code? =


> Decodemodule 1,?incmod
> [-program stuff-]
> End
> =

> .incmod
> INCBIN "MOD.Blah"
> =

> This should work. putting a ? infront of the name of labels returns the=

> address of that label, just like putting an & before a variable name
> returns it's address. (Or is it the other way arround ?)

This is right ^

Or, to think of it in a different way  "?" refers to an address within th=
e
program code, and "&" refers to an address somewhere else in memory.

I always put any INCBIN'd stuff at the very end of the code, and put the
"EVEN" command just before them, to be safe.

