@NODE "Mail_386" "M1.48"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 30 Mar 1999 15:42:31 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 30 Mar 99 15:37:28 +0000
Subject: M1.48
Encoding: 7bit

Hi folks,

Have just uploaded Mildred v1.48 to the support site. It's mainly
another optimisations release, although de-res support has been fully
implemented into the zoom tokens. I've added various versions of
routines to give faster effects in certain cases, such as when the
zoom adders are integers, or when the x adder is 1.0 (for y stretch),
when width is a multiple of 4 or 16 and also the customoffsets
routines are faster too. All the zooms have been optimised and are
about 4 or so fps faster, and particularly the routines for integer x
adder and especially for x adder of 1.0 are very much faster than
otherwise.

The de-resolution effect is one most people have seen before, whereby
the resolution of the image (the size of the pixels basically) is
altered without changing the overall size of the image. Alternatively
it's known as pixellisation. In combination with a customoffsets list
it is possible to have different amounts of de-res on each line of the
screen. Mostly the de-res turns out as running about the same speed as
a normal zoom. A compulsory param has been added to the tokens such as
in MZoom, called DeRes?.w, which is either true or false to do a
de-res or normal zoom.

I also tried to write a new line-draw routine, the innerloop of which
was somewhat more efficient (like 2 or 3 instructions per pixel) but
the necessary use of a divu.w (divide) which is the slowest
instruction in the cpu made the overal thing run slower than the old
method so effectively there is no change to it.

Some scrolls and blits have been sped up a little bit, particularly
the SScroll's and other stencil-copying routines such as the 030 tile
routines. Also the simpleremap mode as in most cases been sped up a
bit.

I was going to wait till I'd done rotation before this release but the
rotation is proving a bit more problematic.

The updated archives and a de-res demo should be online soon,

Enjoy.

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk


---------------------------------------------------------------------
To unsubscribe, e-mail: blitz-list-unsubscribe@netsoc.ucd.ie
For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
