Hi all,

I spent hours to understand how all of this works ... I have problems with
listview from months !

Considere a listview and a GtText gadget : I want the clicked word in the
listview appears in the gadget. Ok : it's easy. It works and when I load a new
list and draw it in the listview, it's ok too. But when I click again, a bad
word appears in the text gadget.

Another thing about listview : the program I attached updates a GTString
gadget clicking in a listview. But, again : 2 problems. When I change the
order of the lines GTString 0,50,... GTTags ... and GTListView ... the result
is really ... surprising ! :-(
And try to change GTString in GTtext : it's doesn't work. But why ?

Thanks a lot.

Cheers,

                           Mathias

--BOUNDARY.7741.2229.269542064.1

; Listview

WBStartup
NoCli

FindScreen 0

NEWTYPE .listview
  pad.w
  string.s
End NEWTYPE

Dim List MyList.listview(15)

GTString 0,50,8,39,100,13,"",0,256,""
GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,GTGadPtr(0,50)
GTListView 0,51,8,-5,100,50,"",0,MyList(),0,0
GTButton 0,52,8,60,40,13,"Reset",0
GTButton 0,53,80,60,40,13,"Fill",0
GTString 0,54,8,44,100,13,"",0,256,""

Window 0,10,10,150,100,$140e,"Test",1,2

AttachGTList 0,0
Repeat
  ev.l=WaitEvent
  If ev.l=$40 OR ev.l=$20
    If GadgetHit=51
      c=EventCode
      GTSetString 0,54,Str$(c)
    EndIf
    If GadgetHit=52
      ClearList MyList()
      GTChangeList 0,51
      GTChangeList 0,51,MyList()
    EndIf
    If GadgetHit=53
      Gosub FillList
      GTChangeList 0,51
      GTChangeList 0,51,MyList()
      FirstItem MyList()
      GTSetString 0,50,MyList()\string
    EndIf
  EndIf
Until ev=$200

CloseWindow 0
Free GTList 0

End

.FillList
  If AddItem(MyList()) Then MyList()\string="Item 0"
  If AddItem(MyList()) Then MyList()\string="Item 1"
  If AddItem(MyList()) Then MyList()\string="Item 2"
  If AddItem(MyList()) Then MyList()\string="Item 3"
  If AddItem(MyList()) Then MyList()\string="Item 4"
Return

--BOUNDARY.7741.2229.269542064.1--




@ENDNODE
