@NODE "Mail_394" "Re: List Arrays!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 3 Mar 1999 00:49:16 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 02 Mar 1999 18:14:48 -0500
Subject: Re: List Arrays!

Hi Loki

On 02-Mar-99, Loki wrote:
> Hello,
> 
>   Is there a difference between #ResetList#() And #FirstItem#()?

Yes - ResetList sets the list to the beginning, with nothing being the
current item.

FirstItem sets the current item to the first item on the list.  Confusing
...

Maybe an example helps.

This will start at the beginning, and go through each item in your list:

ResetList mylist()
While NextItem (mylist())
  blah blah
  blah blah
Wend

=============

This one looks the same, but it will start with the SECOND item on the list
and skip over the first item - because the current item is the first item
before the loop starts. 

If FirstItem (mylist())
  While NextItem (mylist())
    blah blah
    blah blah
  Wend
EndIf

> 
> Just took me an hour to debug my bloody code, after getting the
> wrong end of the stick from the Manual (Lot of sodding help that is)

Yes, the manual is usually no help at all...



                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
