@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_397" "List administration"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 20 Mar 1999 17:22:57 +0000
Date: Sat, 20 Mar 1999 17:22:23 +0000
From: "Andrew McCarthy \(Sysadmin\)" <andrewmc@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Subject: List administration

Hi folks,

I've upgraded and tested ezmlm on netsoc, and it is now possible to have
message moderation and remote administration.

If you, the subscribers, choose to have moderation, you'll have to pick your
moderators yourselves.  Note that:
- You should, ideally, have at least three moderators, bearing in mind
  their position on the globe so that you're not waiting hours for one of them
  to wake up and approve/reject a mail.

- The first moderator who responds will decide if the email is approved or
  rejected. In all cases, the identity of the moderator will remain anonymous
  (unless he/she chooses otherwise) - But IMHO it's common courtesy to identify
  yourself if you reject a mail.

- Any mail sent to blitz-list-owner@netsoc.ucd.ie will go directly to the
  netsoc administrators here, so if there's any complaints about a
  moderator/administrator they will be handled by us.

- Only netsoc administrators can assign the list moderators


Remote administrators will be able to perform tasks such as unsubscribing
broken addresses and editing the ezmlm response files. If you want remote
administrators note that:

- Moderators and remote admins will probably be the same people.

- If a remote admin unsubscribes a member from the list, the user will be
  notified.

- I would be very reluctant to allow anyone outside of Netsoc the ability to
  arbitrarily read the subscriber list.


Other notes
- Footers appended to mails are possible
- If desired, posts from non-members can be automatically rejected 
- Removal/creation of headers (like Reply-To:) is possible


I'm subscribed to the list and will be listening to members opinions on these
topics, so there's no need to mail me directly. Personally I think moderation
is unnecessary, but remote administration would be useful.

Regards,

Andrew.

andrewmc@netsoc.ucd.ie
Netsoc Sysadmin


@ENDNODE
