@NODE "Mail_407" "library include sizes"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 14 Mar 1999 16:31:53 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Mar 1999 10:24:35 -0500
Subject: library include sizes

Hi everybody,

Does anybody know how to determine the "included" size of a library?

What I mean is how much using a command from a particular library will
increase the finished exec size.

This is not the same as the actual on-disk library size, since the bit at
the beginning with the command name stuff, and the part at the end with the
debugger stuff won't be included.

There must be some flags or something inside the library that tell the
compiler what to include/not include.

Anybody know how to find this information?

I want to add it to my source-reading program, so it can tell you how much
size each library will add to your exec.

Oh, in case you missed my other posting, there is a working version of the
source Investigator available on my website...

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
