Subject: library include sizes
Date: 14 Mar 1999 23:55:27
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 14 Mar 99 Curt Esser wrote about 'library include sizes'.

 CE> Does anybody know how to determine the "included" size of a library?

As far as I'm aware, the whole library is linked in at compile time, theref=
ore
the extra file size would be the library size.

What is needed is either an optimiser or a beter compiler system :)

Simon Archer



