    I'm working on a new compiler since a time ago (Do you remember
PhenX ? It's not dead, it's name is Power Basic now :). It now support
recursive expressions (ie: (2*2)+(MouseX+2*(MouseX)))....) and
has a really good linker which include ONLY used functions. Writing an
optimiser for the Blitz 2 library is nearly impossible (not fully :*)
because all adressing is relative or absolute and need the other libs
to be correct. Pffff...

