@NODE "Mail_425" "Libraries"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 17:32:17 +0000
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Oliver Marks
Subject: Libraries
Date: 07 Mar 1999 17:19:20
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 7 Mar 99 Oliver Marks wrote about 'Libraries'.

 OM> Where can i get information on converting libraries so that they can
 OM> be used from with in blitz i do not want to convert anything in
 OM> particular at this time but am just curious how it is done.

It's not really the library itself that gets converted, it's the FD file yo=
u
need in order for Blitz to create it's Function Table.

Basically, once you have the FD file, run FDConvert over it, and give the
output a free library number. The library commands in the FD file get
converted into Blitz commands with the trailing '_'.

I've creatted quite a few library enviroments for Blitz, and they've all wo=
rked
very well.

Simon Archer



@ENDNODE
