Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 8 Mar 1999 11:07:57 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Letter to AF

Why don't we just put in a letter saying:

----------
 There's a new mailing list for Blitz 2, which should replace the current =
one, 
but we have to make sure everybody knows about it first, and starts using =
it. 
To subscribe to the new list send a message to blitz-list-
subscribe@egroups.com, or go to the web page at 
http://www.egroups.com/list/blitz-list.
----------

 That way it's far more likely that we get into the mag, maybe as a space 
filler type thing. I don't see them printing half a page dedicated to the =
start-
up of the new list.

 As for that newsgroup for Blitz, it died off ages ago, and I mean ages. O=
r I 
thought it did, I just had a look and there was someone wandering around, 
apparently alone. So I posted the subscription address of both lists to th=
e 
newsgroup.


