@NODE "Mail_460" "LEGAL RIGTHS FOR BLITZ2"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 10 Mar 1999 19:50:44 +0000
From: Rui Carvalho <grim@ip.pt>
Date: Wed, 10 Mar 1999 19:40:32 +0000
X-SenderInfo: 1; picture="http://www.ip.pt/~ip234558/ddds/grim.gif";
   homepage="Http://www.ip.pt/~ip234558/"; dob=31011977
Organization: Dark Dreams Designs
Subject: LEGAL RIGTHS FOR BLITZ2
Encoding: 8bit

Hello,

It was a year ago that I mail every companies that old Blitz Rights asking for
permission to include copyrighted material on my Source Code site...

Until now I haven't received any response to it (they are all in Hawaii or
something...)

I don't think it would be illegal to give the source code up for learning
purposes (like it happened for Quake I think...) In fact I think it
should be donated so that a new (remodeled) programming language can
be made (just see what happened with LINUX).

Some of the small things that would make Blitz even greater are simple
to implement (I think!) and they are:

o Procedure / Label folder (somewhat like AM*S)
o Cli compiler !!!
o Full keyboard support for the TED
o or Maybe even a new TED?
o Debugging into includes (it's a sod having to cut & paste the other
  code to see what wrong)
o Test option (before compiling)
o Replacement of the old libraries by new updated ones (Nlibs,
  Mildred)
o And above all make it FREE !!!

Just the idea of a Blitz 2000 remodeled by those who really use it
makes me wanna scream... I just can stop the excitement!

BTW: Paul it's blitz-list-subscribe@egroups.com

-- 
Best Regards,
Rui Carvalho ½gRiM╗

