@NODE "Mail_468" "Re: JavaScript Hover NetDOCK"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 3 Mar 1999 11:27:39 +0000
    3 Mar 99 11:15:58 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 3 Mar 1999 11:15:39 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: JavaScript Hover NetDOCK

On 3 Mar 99, at 10:20, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:

> Okay, what does #IDCMP_INTUITICKS and #IDCMP_GADGETHELP do ? And how do
> you use them ?

 #IDCMP_INTUITICKS is a timer thing in intuition. You receive one of these=
 
message every 0.3 of a second (or something), they're normally used for ti=
ming 
the button presses of the arrows on listviews and scrollers. Try this:

WBToScreen 0
AddIDCMP #IDCMP_INTUITICKS
Window 0,0,0,320,200,$100f,"Intuiticks",-1,-1
While ev.l<>#IDCMP_CLOSEWINDOW
    ev=3DWaitEvent
    If ev=3D#IDCMP_INTUITICKS Then Nprint "Tick"
Wend
End

#IDCMP_GADGETHELP is the message you receive when you stop the mouse point=
er 
over a gadget or window for a short time. All gadtools gadgets (under v39+=
) 
have gadgethelp turned on, you just need to turn it on for your applicatio=
n. 
I've got source at home, but someone else will have it before I can send i=
t.

 You get a pointer to the gadget in the message from intuition, which you 
obtain using the EventIAddress command. I think you need the RWE updated 
windowslib.obj to use that command, because it tokenises at home, but not =
here.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn

Last night I lay in bed looking up at the stars in the sky and I
thought to myself, 'Where the hell is the ceiling?!'



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_469" "Re: JavaScript Hover NetDOCK"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 15:19:34 +0000
          Paris Sun, 7 Mar 1999 16:13:41 +0100 (MET)
From: Jean-Marc GIGANDET <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sun, 07 Mar 1999 16:11:59 +0200
Subject: Re: JavaScript Hover NetDOCK
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Mikkel

Here is how to use GadgetHelp.

First : use GTGadgets, as it's not easy to get pointers for standard gadg=
ets.

Second : add an IDCMP of $4000000 to your window (GadgetHelp IDCMP).

Attach an ExtendedGadget structure to your gadgets :
*EX.ExtendedGadget=3DGTGadPtr(#NumGtList,#NumGad)

Then use this :
  *EX\Flags    =3D *EX\Flags | #GFLG_EXTENDED
  *EX\MoreFlags=3D*EX\MoreFlags|#GMORE_GADGETHELP

In your WaitEvent loop get the #IDCMP_GADGETHELP event and test the gadge=
t ID !
  *EX =3D EventiAddress
  GadSelect.l=3DEX\GadGetID
  ...

If you want to test also some intuition gadgets look at this :
   assume *w is the pointer to window address (*w.Window=3Dpeek.l(addr wi=
ndow(#NumWindow))

  ZonL.l=3D*EX\GadgetType AND $F0
  GadHlp$=3D""
  If *EX <> *w
    Select ZonL                        ; here are the tests of the system=
 gadgets
    Case #GTYP_CLOSE
      GadHlp$=3D"Closing window"
    Case #GTYP_WDRAGGING
      GadHlp$=3D"Title and dragbar for window"
    Case #GTYP_WUPFRONT
      GadHlp$=3D"Window to front"
    Case #GTYP_WDOWNBACK
      GadHlp$=3D"Window to back"
    Case #GTYP_SDRAGGING
      GadHlp$=3D"Title and dragbar for screen"
    Case #GTYP_SUPFRONT
      GadHlp$=3D"Screen to front"
    Case #GTYP_SDOWNBACK
      GadHlp$=3D"Screen to back"
    Case #GTYP_SIZING
      GadHlp$=3D"Window sizing"
    Default
      GadSel =3D *EX\GadgetID        ; now here are the tests of your gad=
gets ID
      Select GadSel
      Case ...
      End Select
    End Select
  End If

Regards ...
-- =

HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr
