Subject: Re: Internet version checks

On 04-Mar-99, Gareth Griffiths wrote:
> Hi,   
>   I KNOW this has been asked before, but I was not subscribed to the
> list when the question first appeared.
> 
> IS it possible to check if the users computer is on-line, and if it
is,
> open a connection to a certain IP addy and access a file from it, get
> data from the file, and then disconnect? I want to build ina version
> checker similar to YAM2pr6 so that if I releases a new version of a
> proggy, then it will auto-inform you of the fact. Is this possible?
 
  Yes, use the FTP protocol, if your file is on an FTP Server, or a Web
protocol to get the file- you could get it to grab the new version as
well, and ask if the user wants to install it (or delay it for a
certain time)- you could create a general program for doing this, as
the Amiga really needs some software like this- you could make it
shareware!

