@NODE "Mail_491" "Internet version checks"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 6 Mar 1999 12:17:25 +0000
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Gareth Griffiths
Subject: Internet version checks
Date: 05 Mar 1999 02:53:48
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 3 Mar 99 Gareth Griffiths wrote about 'Internet version checks'.

 GG> IS it possible to check if the users computer is on-line, and if it is=

The first thing that springs to mind is:

If (OpenLibrary_("bsdsocket.library",0) then Online{}

This could fail tho' as the user may not connected even though the library
is available, but it does give a rough indication. Next I would then try to
open an FTP connection with the site in question and see if that succeeds.

Simon Archer



