Just a few ideas.....

I figure the main program is just a database, which store internet address
of files to check, and simply scans for the date of the file and compares it
to the last time you updated your software, and if a new archive is there,
it simply fires of a new task to download it (with options to ASK you
first). The http or ftp is easily sovled..by having the internet address
have http:// or ftp:// infront, to specify which protocol to use.

As for the gui, I figure we could have a mui and non mui interface...if a
couple of people did similar ones, then it`s upto the user to choose.

Rick Hodger claims to have done this already...I`m not sure if he meant...as
in a part of his software (ie, to just update his software) or for anyones
software. If this program is already available..then there isn`t too much
point in doing another one.

Dave



@ENDNODE
