That`s okay...I have a partially working ftp program (shell only) and a
partially working web browser. All I meant to say was...it`ll have
both...and thats how you specify one of the other ;)...as all you basically
do is open tcp/ip connections and pass text commands across it...which I`ll
use my irc parser (yes..another paritally working program) to quickly
decipher the text and decide on the action :). I used to do quite a bit of
telneting and a while back I did some rexx programs for amirc to fetch ftp
files and web pages, so I`m used to the silly internet protocols :).

Personally, I think it`d work better on ftp...as all you do is list the
filename and read the date, and then fetch it if need be....also, most
decent ftp sites support resuming (very handy on huge files) and I don`t
think http does (or does it??...it`s been a long time since I was playing
with tcp/ip).....but I can see that most people have free web space...where
as you don`t get free ftp space often.....

Dave




