@NODE "Mail_496" "Re: Internet version checks"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 09:05:43 +0000
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Sun, 07 Mar 1999 21:55:16 +1300
Subject: Re: Internet version checks

On 05-Mar-99, Simon Archer wrote:
> On 3 Mar 99 Gareth Griffiths wrote about 'Internet version checks'.
> 
>> IS it possible to check if the users computer is on-line, and if
> it is,
> 
> The first thing that springs to mind is:
> 
> If (OpenLibrary_("bsdsocket.library",0) then Online{}
> 
> This could fail tho' as the user may not connected even though the
> library is available, but it does give a rough indication. Next I
would
> then try to open an FTP connection with the site in question and see
if
> that succeeds.
 
  If you're using Miami, you just use the Rexx command IsOnline (like in
this Rexx script) to see if Miami is connected:

ADDRESS MIAMI.1                                                         
                                                                     
MIAMIONLINE = 0                                                        
    IsOnline                                                           
       IF RC = 0 THEN                                                  
            DO                                                         
               OnLine                                                  
                MIAMIONLINE = 1                                        
               END   

   You can also use Paul's #ConnectTCP# function which returns #False#
if the connection attempt failed.
 
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
      A500,DF1:,0.5MC,8.5MF,60HDD,WB3.1 &1.3/2.0 
    A1200,2M,CD-Rom,25/040,200/PPC ,WB3.0 
          
    Project: UDP_Chat [99%]- an Internet multi-player code, test-bed 
      for my game Pyro-Mid. - Aminet: dev/basic/UDP_Chat.lha (V2.1)
         <http://www.ww.co.nz/home/anton/>



@ENDNODE
