I watched as Anton Reinauer hammered "Re: Internet version checks" out on
their keyboard...

>> It can cause no end of problems, if the user has just come offline,
> but
>> the domain's IP address is still cached. It tends to sit for anything
>> up to five minutes trying to connect :/

>  Is that with Miami? Do you have the same problem if you use
> gethostbyname_ rather than connect_ ? I'd be rather interested to know!

'tis Miami indeed.  It's caused when gethostbyname_ returns the cached IP
address to connect to rather than saying "whoops! couldn't find that
address!" and so ConnectTCP{} goes on to try and connect to that IP
address.

