Basically, you use the best ftp command in the world called STAT and give it
a path and file name..and hey presto :)....you don`t need the data
connection..(it passes the info through the control connection) and there is
very little that can go wrong with those 3 commands :), compared to fetching
the actual file...which requires a data connection. (BTW...the only ppl I
know that use the STAT command use telnet...cos it`s fast and less mess than
using LIST....and this should work on all ftp servers...as it is defined in
rfc 959!)..and as I said before...most decent ftp sites have resume (a
brilliant idea when download a HUGE file!!!)...and I haven`t seen resume on
http...or am I mistaken??? (that was my ftp vs http argument!)


Keep smiling,

Dave




