@NODE "Mail_528" "InitRastPort_"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 11 Mar 1999 12:45:20 +0000
From: Toby Zuijdveld <hotcakes@abacus.net.au>
	Blitz List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Thu, 11 Mar 1999 15:09:38 +1000
X-SenderInfo: 1;
   picture="http://www.geocities.com/SunsetStrip/Disco/6865/a1people/tobyzuij.gif"
Organization: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Res=A1stance?=
Subject: InitRastPort_

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.5471960.1
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello,

OK, so I've initialised a #RastPort# using #InitRastPort_#, do I need to =
free it
after I've finished using it?  If so, how the hell?!?

Also as a little bonus, I've been working on the attached routine for a m=
onth. =

Some of you people might find it interesting.  Maybe.

It uses cludges from sources all over the place.  And it's written by me,=

which means it's a complete mess.  It probably doesn't even work, I can't=
 test
it yet.  Off the top of my head, these are the things you'll need :

Mildred
BSS
Stats&Funcs.bb2
DTLocaleLib.bb2
And a few newtypes/constants from the DoMethod picture.datatype example.

The command template is : shapenumber.l=3D#MCacheBlit#{shapename$,xpos.l,=
ypos.l}

It's designed to be a #MBlit# replacement, which also handles loading via=

datatypes, palette remapping and usage of a cache.

Most of it is fairly well #REM#med, I think.

If you do mess around with it, or indeed use it on your own software, be =
sure
to give me any improved versions you've done =3D]

Kind regards
-- =


 ***************
 *** CAT TAG *** "2.2 seconds - that's how fast the train travels..." - M=
r Partington, Physics
 ***************

   _   _ _  __ _  _  /\_ _
 _________\/_________/\___ -- Toby Zuijdveld --
 \____   =AC\/. ______   __/
  |   )  _/\____  \/    \  -EMail : mailto:hotcakes@abacus.net.au-
  |!  |   =AC\    \ \\    \\ - HTTP : http://abacus.net.au/hotcakes
  |___|   //_____ //___ //          [ Last updated : 10=B703=B799 ]
      !___/      \/DTN.\/

--BOUNDARY.5471960.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="MCacheBlit.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Description: BTW, it's pretty big =]

  EndIf

=2Efunctions:
  Statement SetAGARGB{color.l,r.w,g.w,b.w}
    SHARED re(),gr(),bl()
    AGAPalRGB 0,color,r,g,b
    re(color)=3Dr
    gr(color)=3Dg
    bl(color)=3Db
  End Statement
  Function.w GetAGARGB{askedvalue.b,colornum.l}
  ; This is a replacement for the AGARed, AGAGreen and AGABlue
  ; commands.  The values are stored internally by SetAGARGB{},
  ; which sets the palette at the same time and uses a command
  ; template similar to AGAPalRGB.  We use this system because
  ; the standard commands are broken and we don't want to bump
  ; the executable size by introducing a whole new lib (ie all
  ; PaletteInfo related commands).  This routine probably won't
  ; ever be needed, as I don't see any reason why I wouldn't grab
  ; the re(), gr() and bl() values directly.  Hmmm =3D]
    SHARED re(),gr(),bl()
    Select askedvalue
      Case 0
        Pop Select
        Function Return re(colornum)
      Case 1
        Pop Select
        Function Return gr(colornum)
      Case 2
        Pop Select
        Function Return bl(colornum)
      Default
        Pop Select
        Function Return -1
    End Select
  End Function
  Function.l IsColourECS{re.w,gr.w,bl.w}
  ; This function converts the palette entries into ECS shades...
  ; Why?!?  Well, 256 colours isn't much to play around with when
  ; one shape uses 256 shades of blue, for example.  This way it
  ; only uses 16 shades of blue and leaves the program to handle
  ; another 240 colours.  When you think about it, that still
  ; isn't much at all - the ECS palette consists of 4096 colours,
  ; when all 256 are used here, we're still missing out on 3840 of
  ; them!  Oh and sorry about the variable names =3D] This routine
  ; was written 2 years ago.  I code more sensibly now, honest =3D]
    SHARED numcolours
    SHARED r(),g(),b()
    SHARED *sc
    doeshewintheholiday.l=3D((re LSR 4)*$100)+((gr LSR 4)*$10)+(bl LSR 4)=

    winner.l=3D$ffffff
    For gameshow.l=3D1 To numcolours
      contender.l=3D(((r(gameshow) LSR 4)*$100)+((g(gameshow) LSR 4)*$10)=
+(b(gameshow) LSR 4))-doeshewintheholiday
      If contender<0 Then contender=3D-contender
      If winner>contender Then winner=3Dcontender
    Next
    If winner=3D0 Then Function Return -1 Else Function Return 0
  End Function
  Function.l convertbl{variable.l}
    If variable<0 Then variable=3D$100+variable
    Function Return variable
  End Function  ; Convert byte negatives to longword positives!
  Function.l MCacheBlit{shp$,x.l,y.l}
  ; This routine first checks the cache to see if the needed shape
  ; is allready loaded, removes old entries if the cachesize
  ; checks out to be larger than the predefined limit, loads
  ; shapes via datatype if nessessary, converts it to chunky,
  ; stores the chunky image for future faster processing,
  ; allocates a certain amount of screenpens (either half of the
  ; available pens, or half of the images' number of colours,
  ; whichever is less), remaps the image and -FINALLY!!!- blits it
  ; to the currently used bitmap.  I think I covered it all? =3D] It
  ; returns with the allocated MShapenumber so the rest of the
  ; code can manipulate it if it wants, 0 for general failure, -1
  ; for fatal failure (+quit).
    SHARED numcolours,gfxcacheentries,gfxcachesize,gfxcachemaxmem
    SHARED gfxcachemem,lowmem,body$,gadget$,gadgetlocale,doerror
    SHARED tolerance,bgcr,bgcg,bgcb,rp
    SHARED cache(),cachebackup(),shapeused(),shapeusedbackup()
    SHARED re(),gr(),bl()
    SHARED *bmhd,*vm,*sc,*bmp
    db.b=3D1
    For loop.l=3D1 To gfxcacheentries
      If cache(loop)\name=3Dshp$  ; Is this cache entry the shape we need=
?
        Pop For ; Yes!  Then forget the loop and go to blit it
        shp.l=3Dloop
        Goto mcacheblitblitshape
      EndIf ; No!  Then check the next entry
    Next  ; Checks to see if the shape we need is in the cache
    loop=3D1
    While (gfxcachemem>gfxcachemaxmem) OR (gfxcacheentries>#MAX_SHAPES)
      If cache(loop)\shp>0  ; Keep an `error' entry (they are empty anywa=
y...)
        MFreeShape cache(loop)\shp
        shapeused(cache(loop)\shp)=3D0
        gfxcachemem-cache(loop)\size
        gfxcacheentries-1
        CopyMem_ &cache(loop),&cache(loop+1),(gfxcacheentries-loop)*SizeO=
f.cachedata  ; Moves all entries down a notch (fast)
;        For looptwo.l=3Dloop To gfxcacheentries ; Moves all entries down=
 a notch (slow, reliable, the fast way may not work?)
;          cache(looptwo)\shp=3Dcache(looptwo+1)\shp,cache(looptwo+1)\nam=
e,cache(looptwo+1)\size
;        Next
        loop-1
      EndIf
      loop+1
    Wend  ; Checks to see if the the maximum memory limit hasn't been exc=
eeded and if it has, scrubs the oldest entries
    gfxcacheentries+1
    If gfxcacheentries>gfxcachesize
      Dim cachebackup.cachedata(gfxcachesize)
      Dim shapeusedbackup.l(gfxcachesize)
      CopyMem_ &cache(0),&cachebackup(0),gfxcachesize*SizeOf.cachedata  ;=
 Backup the cache (fast, but does it work?)
      CopyMem_ &shapeused(0),&shapeusedbackup(0),gfxcachesize*SizeOf.l
;      For loop=3D1 To gfxcachesize  ; Backup the cache (slow, reliable)
;        cachebackup(loop)\shp=3Dcache(loop)\shp,cache(loop)\name,cache(l=
oop)\size
;      Next
;      For loop=3D1 To gfxcachesize
;        shapeusedbackup(loop)=3Dshapeused(loop)
;      Next
      Dim cache.cachedata(gfxcacheentries)
      Dim shapeused.l(gfxcacheentries)
      CopyMem_ &cachebackup(0),&cache(0),gfxcachesize*SizeOf.cachedata  ;=
 Copy the cache back (fast, but does it work?)
      CopyMem_ &shapeusedbackup(0),&shapeused(0),gfxcachesize*SizeOf.l
;      For loop.l=3D1 To gfxcachesize  ; Copy the cache back (slow, relia=
ble)
;        cache(loop)\shp=3Dcachebackup(loop)\shp,cachebackup(loop)\name,c=
achebackup(loop)\size
;      Next
;      For loop.l=3D1 To gfxcachesize
;        shapeused(loop)=3Dshapeusedbackup(loop)
;      Next
      gfxcachesize=3Dgfxcacheentries
    EndIf ; Backs up the cache if we need to make it larger
    shp=3Dgfxcacheentries
    cache(shp)\name=3Dshp$
    loop=3D1
    While shapeused(loop)
      loop+1
    Wend  ; Assigns a MShapenumber
    cache(shp)\shp=3Dloop
    shapecolours.l=3D0
    title$=3Dshp$+" - "+DTLocaleGetStr{$17,"Loading"}+"...  "
    WindowTitle{#WMAIN,title$,DTLocaleGetStr{2,"Game"}}
    banknum.l=3DBLoad(shp$+".shonky")
    If banknum<>-1  ; Checks to see if the chunky image exists first
      If Peek.s(Start(banknum))=3D"SHC" ; Is it a valid chunkyfile?
      ; I think here would be a good place to get myself organised
      ; with the .shonky structure :
      ;
      ; Offset  Type            Size            Description
      ;
      ;    0    string          4                 "SHC",0
      ;    4      long          4                 X size
      ;    8      long          4                 Y size
      ;   12      long          4                 Number of colours
      ;   16     bytes          (Offset 12)*3     R, G, B values
      ; ((Offset 12)*3)+16  (Offset 4)*(Offset 8) Chunky data
        cache(shp)\size=3DLength(banknum) ; Not just the chunky size, but=
 header+xsize+ysize+palette+chunky size
        shapecolours=3DPeek.l(Start(banknum)+12)  ; We need to figure thi=
s out now so we can get the offset for the chunky data
        If MCludgeShape(cache(shp)\shp,Peek.l(Start(banknum)+4),Peek.l(St=
art(banknum)+8),Start(banknum)+(shapecolours*3)+16)
          Dim r.l(shapecolours), g.l(shapecolours)
          Dim b.l(shapecolours)
          AGAPalRGB 1,shapecolours,0,0,0  ; InitPalette crashes on some m=
achines
          For loop=3D0 To shapecolours-1
            r(loop)=3Dconvertbl{Peek.b(Start(banknum)+16+(loop*3))}
            g(loop)=3Dconvertbl{Peek.b(Start(banknum)+17+(loop*3))}
            b(loop)=3Dconvertbl{Peek.b(Start(banknum)+18+(loop*3))}
            AGAPalRGB 1,loop,r(loop),g(loop),b(loop)
          Next  ; Reads in the palette entries, watching for blitz's stup=
id signed-only bytes
          Erase banknum ; Cludged the chunky and read the palette, we no =
longer need this
          Goto mcacheblitremapshape
        Else
          If lowmem=3D0 ; Don't give the warning twice
            errorsize.l=3Dcache(shp)\size
            Gosub mcacheblitdoerror
          EndIf
        EndIf
      EndIf
      Erase banknum
    EndIf
    *obj.b=3DNewDTObjectA_(&shp$,VarArgs(#DTA_SourceType,#DTST_FILE,#DTA_=
GroupID,#GID_PICTURE,0))
    ; We create the DT Object

    If *obj<>0  ; Is the file readable?

      GetAttr_ #PDTA_BitMapHeader,*obj,&*bmhd
      GetAttr_ #PDTA_ModeID,*obj,&*vm

      ; We get some informations on the picture

      w.l=3D*bmhd\bmh_Width
      h.l=3D*bmhd\bmh_Height
      d.w=3D*bmhd\bmh_Depth
      shapecolours=3DPlanes2Cols{d}

      wi.l=3D((w LSR 4)+1) LSL 4

;      Dim ScrTags.TagItem(13)
;      Rect.Rectangle\MinX=3D0,0,w,h ; For test
;      ScrTags(0)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Width,wi  ; For test
;      ScrTags(1)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Height,h  ; For test
;      ScrTags(2)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Depth,d
;      ScrTags(3)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_DisplayID,0
;      ScrTags(4)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Type,$F
;      ScrTags(5)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Quiet,True
;      ScrTags(6)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_ShowTitle,False
;      ScrTags(7)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Behind,True
;      ScrTags(8)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_DClip,&Rect ; For test
;      ScrTags(9)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Exclusive,False
;      ScrTags(10)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_Draggable,False
;      ScrTags(11)\ti_Tag=3D#SA_AutoScroll,False
;      ScrTags(12)\ti_Tag=3D#TAG_DONE,0
;      ScrTags(13)\ti_Tag=3D#TAG_DONE,0
;
;      If ScreenTags(1," ",&ScrTags(0))  ; Enough memory for opening a dr=
awscreen?  (I don't know how to draw direct to bitmap)
;        ScreensBitMap 1,1 ; Yes!  Then continue with the datatype transf=
er

      *scr._Screen=3DPeek.l(Addr Screen(0))
      ; We get the address of our screen

      InitRastPort_ &rp ; create your rastport
;        *rp._RastPort=3D&*scr\_RastPort
      ; We get the address of our RastPort

      *bmp=3DAllocBitMap_(wi,h,d,65536,0) ; create your bitmap
      rp\_BitMap=3D*bmp ; point rastport to bitmap

      render_here.l=3D&rp

      ginfo.GadgetInfo\gi_Screen=3D*scr,0,0,render_here,rp\Layer
      ginfo\gi_Domain\Left=3D*bmhd\bmh_Left,*bmhd\bmh_Top,w,h
      ginfo\DetailPen=3D0,0
      ginfo\gi_DrInfo=3DGetScreenDrawInfo_(*scr)

      ; We create a GadgetInfo structure

      *gadinfo.GadgetInfo=3D&ginfo

      attrs.l=3DVarArgs(#GA_Left,*bmhd\bmh_Left,#GA_Top,*bmhd\bmh_Top,#GA=
_Width,w,#GA_Height,h,#ICA_TARGET,#ICTARGET_IDCMP,0)

      SetDTAttrsA_*obj,0,0,attrs

      ; We set some attrs to the Object

      DoMethod *obj,#GM_LAYOUT,*gadinfo,0
      ; We draw the Picture on our screen

      *isdrawn.l=3D0

      Repeat                                    ; This loop
        GetAttr_ #DTA_LayoutProc,*obj,&*isdrawn ; wait for the end
      Until *isdrawn=3D0                          ; of the drawing of the=
 pic

      AGAPalRGB 1,shapecolours,0,0,0  ; init of the palette

      *creg.b=3D0

      GetAttr_ #PDTA_ColorRegisters,*obj,&*creg ; We get the color regist=
ers

      Dim r.l(shapecolours), g.l(shapecolours), b.l(shapecolours)

      For i=3D0 To shapecolours-1
        r.l=3DPeek.b(*creg):g.l=3DPeek.b(*creg+1):b.l=3DPeek.b(*creg+2)
        r(i)=3Dconvertbl{r}:g(i)=3Dconvertbl{g}:b(i)=3Dconvertbl{b}
        AGAPalRGB 1,i,r(i),g(i),b(i)
        *creg=3D*creg+3
      Next
      ; This routine create the palette

;        UsePalette{ViewPort(1),1}

      DoMethod *obj,#GM_RENDER,*gadinfo,render_here,1 ; We refresh the pi=
c

;        GetaShape 1,0,0,wi,h
;
;        Free Screen 1
;
;        Free BitMap 1

      DisposeDTObject_ *obj

      If MShape(cache(shp)\shp,wi,h)  ; Got enough memory to convert it t=
o chunky?
        MPlanar16ToShape cache(shp)\shp,*bmp\Planes
        banknum.l=3DReserve((wi*h)+16+(shapecolours*3))
        If banknum<>-1  ; Enough memory to save the shape?  (Not a fatal =
error if no memory this time)
          Poke.s Start(banknum),"SHC"
          Poke.l Start(banknum)+4,wi
          Poke.l Start(banknum)+8,h
          Poke.l Start(banknum)+12,shapecolours
          For loop=3D0 To shapecolours-1
            Poke.b Start(banknum)+(loop*3)+16,r(loop)
            Poke.b Start(banknum)+(loop*3)+17,g(loop)
            Poke.b Start(banknum)+(loop*3)+18,b(loop)
          Next
          CopyMem_ MShapePtr(0,0,cache(shp)\shp),Start(banknum)+16+(shape=
colours*3),wi*h
          BSave shp$+".shonky",banknum
          Erase banknum
        EndIf
      Else  ; No!  Then error me purple!
        If lowmem=3D0 ; Don't give the warning twice
          errorsize.l=3Dw*h
          Gosub mcacheblitdoerror
        EndIf
      EndIf
;      Else  ; No!  Then the usual out of memory thing
;        If lowmem=3D0 ; Don't give the warning twice
;          lowmem=3D1
;          body$=3DDTLocaleGetStr{7,"Out of memory (I need"}+" "+Str$(Int=
((((w*h)/8)*d)/1024)+1)+"K) !!!||"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{8,"This one is pretty fatal I'm afraid"}+=
".|"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{9,"You can TRY to continue as usual, but"=
}+"|"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$a,"I strongly recommend quitting out and=
"}+"|"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$b,"reducing the maximum gfx cache size"}=
+".||"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$c,"Continue  You will not be warned agai=
n"}+"|"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$f,"Halve   Will halve your gfx cache siz=
e"}+"|"
;          body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$d,"Quit      You can save your game firs=
t"}
;          gadget$=3D"Continue|Halve|Quit"
;          gadgetlocale=3D$e
;          MOVEM.l d0-d7/a0-a6,-(a7)
;            GetReg a0,doerror
;            JSR (a0)
;          MOVEM.l (a7)+,d0-d7/a0-a6
;          Select success
;            Case 0
;              cache(shp)\shp=3D-2
;              Erase banknum
;              Pop Select
;              Goto mcacheblitexit
;            Case 2
;              gfxcachemaxmem/2
;              lowmem=3D0
;              body$=3DDTLocaleGetStr{$10,"Your cache has been reduced to=
"}+" "+Str$(Int(gfxcachemaxmem/1024)+1)+"K|"
;              body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$13,"Use the Prefs to set it to this =
size if"}+"|"
;              body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$14,"you continue without further pro=
blems"}+"|"
;              body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$11,"It's currently"}+" "+Str$(Int(gf=
xcachemem/1024)+1)+" "+DTLocaleGetStr{$12,"big"}+"|"
;              gadget$=3D"Continue"
;              gadgetlocale=3D$15
;              MOVEM.l d0-d7/a0-a6,-(a7)
;                GetReg a0,doerror
;                JSR (a0)
;              MOVEM.l (a7)+,d0-d7/a0-a6
;          End Select
;        EndIf
;      EndIf
      FreeBitMap_ *bmp
    Else  ; No!  Then mark this file as bad and don't bother reading it a=
gain
      cache(shp)\shp=3D-1
      Goto mcacheblitexit
    EndIf

mcacheblitremapshape:
    title$+DTLocaleGetStr{$1a,"Remapping"}+"...  "
    WindowTitle{#WMAIN,title$,DTLocaleGetStr{2,"Game"}}
    Use Palette 0
    usecolours.l=3DMin(((2^*sc\dpth)-numcolours)/2,shapecolours/2)
    donotuseanymorethantheseamountofcolours.l=3Dnumcolours+usecolours ; ;=
] It had to be done -somewhere- ;
    For i=3D1 To usecolours-1
      If *sc\dpth<0 ; Ummm, reserved for >8 bit screens, which will be do=
ne later
;        color=3DIsColourAGA{AGAPalRed(i),AGAPalGreen(i),AGAPalBlue(i)}
;        If color=3D0
;          numcolours+1
;          AGAPalRGB 1,numcolours,AGAPalRed(i),AGAPalGreen(i),AGAPalBlue(=
i)
;        EndIf
      Else
        color.l=3DIsColourECS{re(i),gr(i),bl(i)}
        If color=3D0

morepaletteecs:
          If numcolours<Planes2Cols{screendepth}-1
            numcolours+1
          EndIf ; Makes sure no more than the number of the screen's avai=
lable pens are written to
          If (numcolours>16) OR (numcolours<20) Then Goto morepaletteecs =
 ; Keeps the poi ter colours free
          SetAGARGB{numcolours,re(i),gr(i),bl(i)}
        EndIf
      EndIf
    Next
;    If numcolours=3D2^screendepth Then numcolours=3D(2^screendepth)-1
    MTable 0,256
    Poke.b MTablePtr(0),0
    MUseShape cache(shp)\shp
    If *sc\dpth<0 ; Again, this code is reserved for >8 bit screens
;      For j=3D1 To (2^ILBMDepth)-1
;
;againaga:
;        color=3DFindColor(1,AGAPalRed(j),AGAPalGreen(j),AGAPalBlue(j),to=
lerance)
;        If color=3D0 Then db=3D15-db:PalRGB 1,0,db,db,db:Goto againaga
;        ReMap j,color,0
;      Next
    Else
      For j.l=3D1 To shapecolours-1

againecs: ; We don't want it to remap to colour 0, we don't want extra tr=
ansperency =3D] and no pointer colours either!
        color.l=3DFindColor(0,r(j),g(j),b(j),tolerance)
        If color=3D0 Then db=3D1-db:AGAPalRGB 0,0,db*255,db*255,db*255:Go=
to againecs
        For i=3D17 To 19
          If color=3Di Then db=3D1-db:AGAPalRGB 0,i,db*255,db*255,db*255:=
Goto againecs
        Next
        Poke.b MTablePtr(0)+j,color
      Next
      AGAPalRGB 0,0,bgcr,bgcg,bgcb
      For i=3D17 To 19
        AGAPalRGB 0,i,re(i),gr(i),bl(i)
      Next
      MReMapShape MTablePtr(0),cache(shp)\shp
    EndIf

mcacheblitblitshape:
    If (cache(shp)\shp<1) OR (cache(shp)\name=3D"") OR (cache(shp)\size<1=
)
      cache(shp)\shp=3D0,"",0
    Else
      MBlit cache(shp)\shp,x,y  ; Finally!!!  All that for just this, see=
ms like such a waste =3D]
    EndIf ; Just as one last failsafe before the routine returns with a v=
alid MShapenumber

mcacheblitexit:
    If cache(shp)\shp>0 ; Was the shape successfully stored?
      title$=3DDTLocaleGetStr{$18,"Playing"}
      WindowTitle{#WMAIN,title$,DTLocaleGetStr{2,"Game"}}
      Function Return cache(shp)\shp  ; Yes!  Then give the program the M=
Shapenumber
    Else  ; No!  Then give the program nada!
      If cache(shp)\shp=3D-2 Then Function Return -1
      title$=3DDTLocaleGetStr{$19,"Error with"}+" "+shp$+"!"
      WindowTitle{#WMAIN,title$,DTLocaleGetStr{2,"Game"}}
      Function Return 0
    EndIf

mcacheblitdoerror:
    lowmem=3D1
    body$=3DDTLocaleGetStr{7,"Out of memory (I need"}+" "+Str$(Int(errors=
ize/1024)+1)+"K) !!!||"
    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{8,"This one is pretty fatal I'm afraid"}+".|"
    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{9,"You can TRY to continue as usual, but"}+"|"
    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$a,"I strongly recommend quitting out and"}+"|"
    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$b,"reducing the maximum gfx cache size"}+".||"
    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$c,"Continue  You will not be warned again"}+"|"=

    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$f,"Halve   Will halve your gfx cache size"}+"|"=

    body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$d,"Quit      You can save your game first"}
    gadget$=3D"Continue|Halve|Quit"
    gadgetlocale=3D$e
    MOVEM.l d0-d7/a0-a6,-(a7)
      Call doerror
    MOVEM.l (a7)+,d0-d7/a0-a6
    Select success
      Case 0
        cache(shp)\shp=3D-2
        Erase banknum
        Pop Select
        Pop Gosub
        Goto mcacheblitexit
      Case 2
        gfxcachemaxmem/2
        lowmem=3D0
        body$=3DDTLocaleGetStr{$10,"Your cache has been reduced to"}+" "+=
Str$(Int(gfxcachemaxmem/1024)+1)+"K|"
        body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$13,"Use the Prefs to set it to this size if=
"}+"|"
        body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$14,"you continue without further problems"}=
+"|"
        body$+DTLocaleGetStr{$11,"It's currently"}+" "+Str$(Int(gfxcachem=
em/1024)+1)+" "+DTLocaleGetStr{$12,"big"}+"|"
        gadget$=3D"Continue"
        gadgetlocale=3D$15
        MOVEM.l d0-d7/a0-a6,-(a7)
          Call doerror
        MOVEM.l (a7)+,d0-d7/a0-a6
    End Select
    Return
  End Function
  Function.b InitDisplay{Title$}

--BOUNDARY.5471960.1--




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_529" "Re: InitRastPort_"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 11 Mar 1999 12:58:48 +0000
 Thu, 11 Mar 1999 12:54:57 GMT
    11 Mar 99 12:56:52 0
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
        Blitz List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Thu, 11 Mar 1999 12:55:18 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: InitRastPort_

> Hello,
> 
> OK, so I've initialised a #RastPort# using #InitRastPort_#, do I need to
> free it after I've finished using it?  If so, how the hell?!?

You only need to free it if you have allocated memory for it. i.e. if you =
done:

DEFTYPE.RastPort rp
InitRastPort_ &rp

then you don't need to free it. If however, you done this:

DEFTYPE.RastPort *rp
*rp=3DAllocMem_(SizeOf.RastPort, #MEMF_PUBLIC|#MEMF_CLEAR)
InitRastPort_ *rp

then you would need to add the line "FreeMem_ *rp,SizeOf.RastPort at the e=
nd 
when you have finished playing about with it.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn

Last night I lay in bed looking up at the stars in the sky and I
thought to myself, 'Where the hell is the ceiling?!'



