@NODE "Mail_531" "Re: Im New Hi all"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 19 Mar 1999 21:24:35 +0000
From: Rui Carvalho <grim@ip.pt>
Date: Fri, 19 Mar 1999 21:17:05 +0000
X-SenderInfo: 1; picture="http://www.ip.pt/~ip234558/ddds/grim.gif";
   homepage="Http://www.ip.pt/~ip234558/"; dob=31011977
Organization: Dark Dreams Designs
Subject: Re: Im New Hi all
Encoding: 8bit

Hello nickpatts

Somewhere nickpatts wrote:
n > Hi just testing to see if my emails get on the list

n > Im quite new to blitz but i would like to know if its possible to make a
n > program that can make executeble programs like the self viewing picture type
n > thing if so how

Blitz programs are stand alone executables and it is possible to include image
and sound on that executable with the incbin command. It is also possible to
use system libraries, 3rd party libraries and even your own libs in Blitz has
well has 68000 assembler code...

I advise you to colect some source code from Blitz sites and learn from it,
change it and mess around with it... There's nothing like breaking stuff and
than glue it back together to learn ;)

Like any language it will take some time for you to get the hang of Blitz, I
myself only realised it's full potencial when I joined the Blitz List and
started to see what could be done!

Feel free to post your doubts it's the only way to learn!

-- 
Best Regards,
Rui Carvalho ½gRiM╗

