encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: IFF Animations

> I wont work for anything but floppy that way. This is because blitz
> mode kills the O/S from running and that is what you nead.  Of couse
> you could jump back and forth from blitz mode to Amiga mode.  That
> would just stop all action for short while.

You can use QAmiga mode, which lets you load stuff etc, but still has the =
Blitz 
display active, so you can still draw to it. But loading rfom floppies and=
 HD 
is the same, just HD is faster.

> Programing support of HD is _lot_ hard work and probley wont work with 3=
.5
> when it comes out.  Then is so easy to write it for floppy then? Well it

Eh?

 Using HD is easy, just makesure you reference stuff from your own directo=
ry 
using PROGDIR:. OS3.5 (if that's what the 3.5 reference was to) isn't goin=
g to 
be that much different from 3.1, just extensions to the filing system (i.e=
.  
bigger HDs, CDROM support etc) and stuff for RTG/RTA and PowerPC. Remember=
 that 
you need OS3.1 on ROM to use it. Blitz and its programs won't cease to wor=
k on 
OS3.5.


