@NODE "Mail_537" "I need help on stack useage methods"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 1 Mar 1999 16:28:58 +0000
From: Jake Frederick <gonzo@acadia.net>
Date: Mon, 01 Mar 1999 11:24:50 +0500
Subject: I need help on stack useage methods

One of my friends has a question for all of you assembly programmers on the
list:

  I am reletively new to assembler programming, in fact I just started a few
weeks ago, but I seem to be having alot fo trouble with stack handling. I can
push a value onto the stack (move.l d0,-(a7)) and I can call it back (move.l
(a7+),a0) but I am unable to dynamically handle stack values. In blitz, when
you go into an assm block yo need to store the d's and a's in a7 (blitz's
stack) but I would like to be able to store values in a stack (preferably the
blitz stack). Is there an easy methode for grabbing "random" values o a
specific value out of the stack?

-- 
-If the doors of perception were cleansed everything would appear to man as it
truly is, infinite.-



@ENDNODE
