@NODE "Mail_539" "Re: I need Blitz Basic now"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 20 Mar 1999 12:52:56 +0000
From: "David McMinnd" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Sat, 20 Mar 1999 12:51:12 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: I need Blitz Basic now

> Any clues where I can buy it?

Don't know about Canada. You could maybe get the demo version (from 
Aminet/dev/basic) until you manage to find the full version, although you =
won't 
be able to create standalone executables. If possible, try to get the Ulti=
mate 
Blitz Basic CD (assuming you have a CD drive) as you get Blitz and Blitz 
Support Suite.

 And as a side question, could people tell me where you can buy Blitz and/=
or 
the BSS in different countries (I know about UK).

> Is Acid Software still in business?

 No.

> What's the most recent version available?

Blitz2.1, SuperTed 2.52, REDDebugger. You need the Blitz support suite for=
 the 
last two, although there is a freebie version of SuperTed 2.24 and also th=
e 
LESDebugger 1.21 (basically the same as REDDebugger) on Aminet.


