@NODE "Mail_544" "Re: Help! i need CD32 PAD information"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 30 Mar 1999 22:12:10 +0100
From: "Evan Tuer" <et@enterprise.net>
Organization: !
Date: 30 Mar 99 20:46:57 +0100
Subject: Re: Help! i need CD32 PAD information
Encoding: 7bit

> Hello blitzers
> 
> I need information on how the CD32 Pad works...
> 
> I know how a joystick with  two button works but i haven't any idea on how
> the others button in the cd32 pad works...

Uh-oh, don't go there..  The others are connected to a shift register,
which is clocked into a spare synchonous serial register on CIA-b, as
far as I can work out.  I made a circuit to use that port, and it
didn't work very well.  But then I found out that the CD32 controllers
don't work very well anyway, you get spurious triggering, and it's
just generally dodgy.  I can't tell you the circuit because I dug it
out of my breadboard a while ago :(  

If you just want to add extra buttons to your amiga, best way is to
use I2C.library from aminet, that works well with Blitz.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
