For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_545" "Re: Help! i need CD32 PAD information"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 31 Mar 1999 17:14:01 +0000
Date: Wed, 31 Mar 1999 18:00:39 +0100
From: d.boaz@virgin.net
Subject: Re: Help! i need CD32 PAD information
Encoding: 7bit

Christian Uceda wrote:
> 
> Hello blitzers
> 
> I need information on how the CD32 Pad works...
> 
> I know how a joystick with  two button works but i haven't any idea on how
> the others button in the cd32 pad works...
> 
> can any one help me?????

	If you just want to use a CD32 Pad here is what it says
	in my Blitz manual.
	
	---------------
	GameB(Port#)
	---------------
	GameB returns the button states of CD32 style game controllers.
	The values of all buttons pressed are added together to make up
	the value returned by GameB. To check a certain button is down a
	logical AND should be performed, buttonvalue AND returnvalue will
	evaluate to 0 if the button is not held down.
	The button values are:

		Play/Pause	1
		Reverse		2
		Forward		4
		Green		8
		Yellow		16
		Red		32
		Blue		64

	Hope this helps, but I haven`t used this command my self so I don`t
	know how good it is, any bugs etc.

Cyas

Dave


