Andrew Bruno
abruno@zeta.org.au




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_547" "Re: Help with loading codes from BUM's...."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 23 Mar 1999 11:42:37 +0000
From: "David McMinn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 23 Mar 1999 11:40:52 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Help with loading codes from BUM's....

> I decided to look at a few of the examples off the bum's, but often when=
 I
> load a program (appended either .bb or .bb2) I get an error:  Can't load
> resident".

 Once you have clicked OK to get past the error, go into the Compiler menu=
 then 
select the Options item. In the Residents box, you will find the names of =
the 
files that Blitz is trying to load but cannot. Usually these will be 
blitzlibs:amigalibs.res or blitzlibs:bb2objtypes.res. If they do not have =
the 
blitzlibs: volume name, try putting it in.

 If that doesn't work, make sure that you have a blitzlibs: directory set =
up - 
normally inside the Blitz2 directory, or in the same directory as it, and =
that 
you have a valid assign to that directory. The .res files should be in the=
re. 
If they are not, then they are on the Ultimate Blitz Basic CD (I think tha=
ts 
what you have?) in the Extras/Blitzlibs drawer, along with some other usef=
ul 
stuff which the crappy install script doesn't install (my fixed version do=
es 
tho).


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
 dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk
  http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn
             ICQ=3D16827694
I love the smell of Napalm in the morning.



@ENDNODE
