Well, it is also on the Ultimate Blitz CD.  The problem is that whoever p=
ut
the CD together apparently just took all the various disks (Blitz 2.1
disks, BSS disks, BUM's 9 & 10 disks, and some other stuff) and slapped
everything onto a CD.

They didn't bother to organize anything or alter the install scripts, so
it's very confusing to get it all installed correctly.

The Blitz 2.1 install script doesn't install the resident files or any of=

the 3rd party libs that come with Blitz 2.1...

You guys who are missing resident files or have commands that won't
tokenize, please look in the "Extras" drawer on the CD.  Here you will fi=
nd
all the stuff that should be in your "Blitzlibs:" directories, but wasn't=

installed.  Including the resident files, and all the 3rd party libraries=
=2E

Copy over everything from this directory that is not already in your
Blitzlibs:  directories to the same places in your Blitz directory  (if y=
ou
have installed BSS, DO NOT copy over any of the RI libraries!)

Now, copy over any new or updated libraries found in the BUM 9 & 10
directories  (again, NO RI libraries!)

Finally, re-make your DefLibs if you use one, and you should be all set.

David McMinn has made a corrected installer script for the Ultimate Blitz=
 CD
-
the easiest solution might be to get this, and just re-install the whole
thing...


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
