@NODE "Mail_559" "Hacker trouble"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 1 Mar 1999 16:12:04 +0000
From: Gareth Griffiths <gaz@jokerd.idps.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 01 Mar 1999 16:07:01 +0100
Organization: Joker Developments
Subject: Hacker trouble

Hi,   
   Is it possible to 'hack' into a program executable and change data in it.
I want to make a Registration Code Generator for NetDOCK-2 and I don't want
to re-compile the src. every time someone registers.

Is it possible to do something similar to NewZAP and move to a specified
location in the executable, and then print data to it.

i.e. part of an executable looks like this say:

<- the hex part in NewZAP ->  < ASC Part >
0000 2748 0019 2749 0020 2750 BLAHBLAHBLAH

is it possible to change it to something else via a blitz prog?

Also, I can save out data to files (like the ND-2 settings) and they are in
normal ASCII format. Is it possible to save them out so that they appear in
HEX mode when viewed with DOPUS' SmartRead command?

Cya.
