Le 01-Mars-99, Gareth Griffiths a =E9crit:

>Hi,   =

>   Is it possible to 'hack' into a program executable and change data in=
 it.
>I want to make a Registration Code Generator for NetDOCK-2 and I don't w=
ant
>to re-compile the src. every time someone registers.

Yes unfortunately it's very easy to crack some data like this.
If you want to protect your Registration Code Generator against some =

little crackers, you must crypt this with the blitz Encrypt function or =

other algorithm like RSA or PGP or the Amiga.lib function ACrypt who's =

a one-way encryption.
But no program are longer protected against big crackers :(( =


>Is it possible to do something similar to NewZAP and move to a specified=

>location in the executable, and then print data to it.

I don't know if NewZap can change some data but with AZap or other
aminet editor you can modify all what you want.  =


