@NODE "Mail_566" "Hacker trouble"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 3 Mar 1999 00:47:19 +0000
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Gareth Griffiths
Subject: Hacker trouble
Date: 03 Mar 1999 00:33:28
encoding: quoted-printable

On 1 Mar 99 Gareth Griffiths wrote about 'Hacker trouble'.

 GG> i.e. part of an executable looks like this say:
 GG> <- the hex part in NewZAP ->  < ASC Part >
 GG> 0000 2748 0019 2749 0020 2750 BLAHBLAHBLAH

Try something like this (from memory):

...

#PositionInFile =3D $23 ; set this to the byte to change
x =3D $10 ; value to set byte to

If OpenFile(0,"env:ND2.prefs")
  ; file opened OK
  FileOutput 0 ; make sure data goes in the right place :)
  FileSeek 0,#PositionInFile
  Print chr$(x)
  CloseFile 0
Else
  ; file didn't open
EndIf

 GG> Also, I can save out data to files (like the ND-2 settings) and they
 GG> are in normal ASCII format. Is it possible to save them out so that
they
 GG> appear in HEX mode when viewed with DOPUS' SmartRead command?

You need to use the dos.library calls for that:

...

; make Amigalibs.res resident for this one

fh.l =3D Open_("env:ND2.prefs",#MODE_NEWFILE)
If fh ; file opened OK
  FPutC_ fh,0
  PutStr_ fh,"This is some text"
  Close_ fh
Else
  ; file didn't open
EndIf



