@NODE "Mail_574" "Re: GTStrings (again)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Fri, 12 Mar 1999 06:59:31 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Mar 1999 00:54:37 -0500
Subject: Re: GTStrings (again)

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1747959768.2

Hi Tony

On 11-Mar-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:
> On Thu, 11 Mar 1999 04:00:25 -0500 Curt Esser said:
>>  Hi Tony
>>  
>>  On 10-Mar-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:
>> > Hi,
>> > 
>> > Is there any way to tell which gadget (if any) has the cursor in it?
>>  
>>  When the GTstringGadget is selected (cursor in it) you will get a
>>  GadgetDown message ($20)
>>  
>>  When it is exited, you get GadgetUp ($40)
> I've had problems getting GadgetDown with a string (Works perfectly
> with buttons), but that won't fully solve my problem.

Try the attached code.  It gets GadgetDown if the string is clicked into,
or
tab-cycled into.
> 
> What I'm looking for is an idea of how to loop through the gadget list
> and find the active one.

No need to loop - If the event was gadgetdown, and GadgetHit was one of
your
strings, that's the active one.  If the event was something else, or some
other gadget was hit, then none of the strings are active.

If you don't want your program to stop with the "WaitEvent" code, just
substitute "Event" instead.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1747959768.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="StringTest.asc"

WBStartup
WBenchToFront_
FindScreen 0

#Str1 = 0
#Str2 = 1
#Str3 = 2
#info = 3

#TextBelow = 8
#Immediate =$80

GTString    0,#Str1,14,11,382,18,"String 1",#TextBelow|#Immediate,256,""
GTString    0,#Str2,14,55,382,18,"String 2",#TextBelow|#Immediate,256,""
GTString    0,#Str3,14,99,382,18,"String 3",#TextBelow|#Immediate,256,""
GTText      0,#info,14,145,382,18,"Information",#TextBelow,""

LoadFont 0,"topaz.font",8
*gtscr.Screen = Peek.l (Addr Screen(0))
offy.b = *gtscr\WBorTop + *gtscr\_RastPort\TxHeight +1
Window 0,130,40,438,193 + offy,15,"GT String Gadgets",1,2
CatchDosErrs
WindowFont 0
offx.b = WLeftOff
AttachGTList 0,0

Repeat
  ev.l = WaitEvent
  If EventWindow=0
    Select ev
      Case $20            ;gadget down message was recieved
        Select GadgetHit
          Case #Str1
            GTSetString 0,#info,"String Gadget #1 is active"
          Case #Str2
            GTSetString 0,#info,"String Gadget #2 is active"
          Case #Str3
            GTSetString 0,#info,"String Gadget #3 is active"
        End Select

      Default             ;not a gadgetdown, therefore none of the
                          ;strings are active

        GTSetString 0,#info,"No string gadget is active"

    End Select

  EndIf
Until ev=$200 AND EventWindow = 0

End

--BOUNDARY.1747959768.2--




@ENDNODE
