Hello Luca
     Hiya, Luca... ,on 27-Mar-99 you mailed me about: GTListViews! So I`ma reply`in...

[=> Hi Blitzers,
[=> 
[=> I'd like to know why the following code causes a GURU (#$80000003) on
[=> 68000/68010 machines (A500/A600):

A discription of the Guru

680x0 EXCEPTION:
 ACPU_AddressErr: Address error

DESCRIPTION:
 Illegal address access. Most of the time this is caused by an attempt to
read or write a word or longword from or at an uneven address. On the 
020 and better CPU's this means that the processor tried to prefetch
an instruction from an uneven address.

(Taken from Guru 3.02)


[=> The problem seems to be in one of the following lines (or both):
[=> 
[=>  GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,0
[=> 
[=>  GTSetAttrs 2,51,#GTLV_Selected,3
[=> 
[=> 
[=> Could you please help me?
[=> 
[=> 
[=> 
[=> 
Regards

there is nothing wrong with the code as far as I can see!  Maybe it's Wtag
that is causing the problem!  Try using the standard Window command!  Also,
have you tried compiling the program on the A600 itself?
