On 26-Mar-99, BootBlock/s^D wrote:

>> The problem seems to be in one of the following lines (or both):
>> =

>>   GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,0
>> =

>>   GTSetAttrs 2,51,#GTLV_Selected,3

>Isn't either GTTags or GTSetAttrs (GTTags I think most probable) OS 3.0
>only?

Well, here is what the documentation about the GTLV_ShowSelected tag says=

  GTLV_ShowSelected (struct Gadget *) - NULL to have the currently
  selected item displayed beneath the listview under V37 or with
  a highlight bar in V39. If not NULL, this is a pointer to
  an already-created GadTools STRING_KIND gadget to have an
  editable display of the currently selected item. If the tag is
  not present, the currently selected item will not be displayed. (V36)

I didn't even know that under V37 it displayed (or at least it should) th=
e selected item beneath the listview instead of using a highlight bar as =
under V39. Anyway it should work but it doesn't.

>I also see in the example that you open the window AFTER setting the
>gadgets up. I
>haven't used WindowTags before, you should be opening the window BEFORE
>the gadgets.

I've never had problems so far by doing like this, but if there is someon=
e who can try this on an A600 (I cannot unfortunately) I'd be very gratef=
ul.



-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

