Hello Luca,

On the 28th of March 1999, Luca Carminati cried out in desperation...

> Really isn't there anyone who can test (and maybe compile) my code on an A600? I've
> attached it again just in case.

I tried it out on my A500+ and got the same result as Anton, but if you move the line...

GTSetAttrs 2,51,#GTLV_Selected,3

...to just after the line...

AttachGTList 2,2

...then it works fine. I'm not sure why this works on 3.1 and not 2.0 in it's original
state. Maybe 2.0 handles GTLists differently, as it would seem logical that you
cannot alter a gadget's attributes until it exists, ie. it's attached to a window.
I hope that helps anyway.


Regards,
Scott

scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk



