@NODE "Mail_608" "GTListViews"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 31 Mar 1999 03:47:39 +0100
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Luca Carminati
Subject: GTListViews
Date: 31 Mar 1999 03:38:49
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 29 Mar 99 Luca Carminati wrote about 'GTListViews'.

 LC> This behaviour is strange but yours is an interesting new. I'm just
 LC> curious: The gadtools doc says that under 2.0 the selected item is
 LC> shown in a text type gadget (automatically created) and under 3.0 it=
 is
 LC> just highlighted (no text gadget). Is that true?

Yes, that's true, under 2.0x the text gadget created underneath the Listvie=
w
is read only. If you want it to be editable, you need to specify the addres=
s
of an already created string gadget. This string gadget is then automatical=
ly
centered directly directly under the listview. This applies for both OS 2.0=
x and
3.x.

As a side note BlitzGUIGen will create these gadgets for you, and any other=
 Blitz
