On 29-Mar-99, Mikkel L=F8kke wrote:

>Hello Luca.

Hi Mikkel.

>> I'm sorry I have to contradict you, Ashley, but I know with certainty =

>> that ListViews are OS2 too. I've got the 'AMIGA ROM Kernel Reference =

>> Manual' V36/37 (it was written when OS3 was not even born) and it =

>> talks about ListViews. Just some tags are OS3+ only, but 'GTLV_
>> ShowSelected' and 'GTLV_Selected' do are OS2. Moreover I coded other =

>> tools with ListViews without 'GTLV_ShowSelected' and 'GTLV_Selected' =

>> and they perfectly work on A600-V37.

>Yes, but like it said (with big childish letters) in the AutoDocs if you=
 =

>use GTLV_ShowSelected (Or whatever) using OS2 YOU HAVE TO GIVE IT A =

>POINTER TO A GTSTRING TYPE GADGET ! Do that and it works, (I think there=
 =

>is even an example of it in the manual) I know I used to have an A600.

No. Here is what my 'AMIGA ROM Kernel Reference Manual' OS2 says:

  GTLV_ShowSelected
    Use this tag to show the currently selected entry displayed
    underneath the listview. Set its value to NULL to get a read-only
    (TEXT_KIND) display of the currently selected entry or set it to a
    pointer to an already-created GadTools STRING_KIND gadget....

This means you can set a NULL value of the tag to see a text gadget benea=
th the listview without having to create it beforehand. On the other hand=
, James has proved it's just like that. But don't worry, you remain the B=
IG GENIUS you are.

>> Really isn't there anyone who can test (and maybe compile) my code on =

>> an A600? I've attached it again just in case.

>No. I don't think anyone who takes themselves seriously would have an =

>A600. (I swapped mine for a copy of settlers)

My nephew still has an A600. And you can be sure he takes himself serious=
ly.

Bye...



-- =

