@NODE "Mail_616" "GTGetAttrs"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 17:33:58 +0000
From: bml@thenet.co.uk (Simon Archer)
X-FTN-To: Jean-Marc GIGANDET
Subject: GTGetAttrs
Date: 07 Mar 1999 17:15:45
X-newsreader: Spot 1.3b #1534
encoding: quoted-printable

On 7 Mar 99 Jean-Marc GIGANDET wrote about 'GTGetAttrs'.

 JMG>    GTMXStat.l =3D GTGetAttrs(NumGadList,NumGTMXGad,#GTMX_Active)
 JMG>    GTCycleStat.l =3D GTGetAttrs(#NumGadList,#NumGTCyGadget,#GTCY_Acti=
ve)

Unfortunately, (I'm sure I read somewhere) the GTGetAttrs() command in Blit=
z
is OS3.0+. If you are planning on supporting OS2.0x as well, the EventCode
command returns the same information when the eventloop detects a gadgethit=
.

Simon Archer



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_617" "Re: GTGetAttrs"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 7 Mar 1999 15:17:32 +0000
          Paris Sun, 7 Mar 1999 16:13:39 +0100 (MET)
From: Jean-Marc GIGANDET <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sun, 07 Mar 1999 16:02:39 +0200
Subject: Re: GTGetAttrs
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Rostislav

Here is an example for GTMX gagdets :

   GTMXStat.l =3D GTGetAttrs(NumGadList,NumGTMXGad,#GTMX_Active)
Now you can use the result GTMXStat where you want. =


Here is an other example with GTCycle :

   GTCycleStat.l =3D GTGetAttrs(#NumGadList,#NumGTCyGadget,#GTCY_Active)

#GTMX_Active and #GTCY_Active are constants figuring in Amigalibs.res.

If you want more, tell me so.

Regards
-- =

HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr
A1200 030/28 + 68881 + 8 Mo + Quantum 635 Mo + Wd 60 Mo + M1438S + Deskje=
t 690C + UsR 33600.
HURRICANE, TURRICAN, well, that's a good mix. Both should visit Redmond .=
