> the Dpaint or Ppaint rotate brush command to do the rotations, and then
> tidy each one up by hand :-)

GTA has a lot of cars (thats one of it's best features) so if you have
over 30 cars with at least 32 rotations you'll have almost 1000 fairly
large shapes. Seems like quite a waste of memory for a rather poor
rotation effect. I think the rotation will have to be real-time. The
GTA engine is half-decent because it had lots of cars with very smooth
rotation. Cut down on either of those features and you`ve lost the
point!

Cheers,

Paul


