Hello Dobbin

SESEM:>> Considered ray-traced images? I wouldn't mind having a
SESEM:>> go at a few images with POVPPC for that purpose. How
SESEM:>> many stages of rotation do there need to be for the cars?
SESEM:>> (ie 8,16,32, more?),

I was hoping to use the rotate command to get a max. of 360 stages, but I've
tried it and I can't get it to work. So I think i'll stick with 16/32
stages. Probably 32, looks smoother.

SESEM:>> Also, do you have a specific palette already set out for
SESEM:>> the graphics? Or, are the 1st 32 colours just going to
SESEM:>> layed out for the car graphics, and the top 32 colours
SESEM:>> for the scenery?

There will be a standard 64-col palette, 32 for the cars, 32 for the city.
The 32 car cols will be standard, which could cause problems with car
designers, but it is the only way I can see. I have a pretty bog standard
Amiga, so I want to be able to test it on my machine!!!!

SESEM:>> And, what sort of top-down projection are you thinking
SESEM:>> of. Ie, should it appear as though the viewer is looking
SESEM:>> straight down at 90' on the cars, or, do you see them
SESEM:>> looking down from slightly off towards the lower part

Straight 90 at the cars, like High Octane and Max Rally/OverDrive/Turbo
Trax.

SESEM:>> Any and all should be relatively easy to do with POV, and
SESEM:>> should look purty darn good ;)

Yeah, but can u do it in 32 cols, AND make it use not lots of mem?? I am
aiming for the min. system reqs as 4mb RAM, 020, and AGA. 

BTW, any ideas for the car-rotation?
Cheerz.
