@NODE "Mail_659" "Re: Grand Theft AMiGA"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 20 Mar 1999 01:33:24 +0000
Date: Sat, 20 Mar 1999 14:32:21 +1300
From: Julian Kinraid <jkinraid@clear.net.nz>
X-Accept-Language: en-GB,en
Subject: Re: Grand Theft AMiGA
Encoding: 7bit

Gareth Griffiths wrote:

[huge snip]

> BTW, any ideas for the car-rotation?

Well, with a rotation, you are taking pixels from the source, and
finding where to put them in the destination.  Because you know the size
of the cars beforehand, and the angle of rotation, you might be able to
create some lookup tables that tell you where you should put the pixels
from the source into the destination. 

If the cars are all different sizes, then that might negate that idea,
but the fact you know the angle of the rotation beforehand (32 steps)
might let you speed up a normal rotation somehow.

--
Julian Kinraid ....... jkinraid@clear.net.nz ....... ICQ:17257217


@ENDNODE
