<snip>

Maybe My imagination is too active or something, but why don't you do the
cars in realtime 3d and texture map them, then slap em on top of your
2D background map (aka resident evil style). The cars would be so small that
it should run reasonbly quickly. The only downside of course is actually
doing the 3d engine which is hellluva complicated :( And you'll prolly need
to do it in ASM for real speed :((

Then again, when you think about it, NAPALM is really just the same type of
game right? It probably has about the same number of shapes (oh yes, lets
not forget the buildings). All the shapes are pre-rotated and stored right?
 And who moaned when they were told it needs 16MB to run? 

a 16MB Simm would cost you about Ż25, thats half the price of a playstation
game :-)))

One more thing, I don't mean to sound negative, but how are you going
to get past the Zoom In/out trick? I know it's not essential, but you just
don't wanna be zoomed right in going at 100 Mph !  And if you zoom too far
out it will look tragic in low-res.

Anyway, best of luck, It sounds like it's gonna be a cool game:)

C-ya!





