Hello Gareth.

On 18-Mar-99, Gareth Griffiths wrote:

> I have just started to work on a Grand Theft Auto clone for our fave ho=
me
> computer. I require help:

>  Car graphics (16/32c Lowres)

You mean 256 colour, no doubt.

>  City graphics (16x16 blocks 64c Lowres)

Once again, you would want to go for the 256 colour option.

>  Car names

Easy, just do what GTA does. Look in a car catalog, and find amusing name=
s that sound like the names of real car brands. Or even better, get a spo=
nsorship from Rover, Aston Martin, Morris, etc...

>  City names

Here's a really brill idea. Get a city map, scan it and basically just co=
nvert it to something you can use in a game. It's the big thing these day=
s.

>  City designs

See above.

>  The name for the game!!

How about "The drive arround killing people for fun game ?" :o>

>  I also need some code to rotate a car shape (using the Rotate command)=

> whenever the player moves his joystick left/right. ie. when you move it=

> right, rotate it a bit clockwise.   =


Okay, here's the deal. Get your graphics dude to build the model in 3D, a=
nd raytrace it rotatinf though 360 degrees (in 64 or 128 intervals, like =
sami suggested), then use Mildred for everything else.

> I expect this project will generate a fair bit of interest. A number of=

> miggy owners like GTA as far as I can see.

Well, you where right about the interest thing. But possibly wrong about =
the GTA thing. GTA is fun for a bit. Then you've done everything there is=
 to do, so you chuck it in the bin. You need to do something really excel=
lent. (I suggest a non-linear gameplay engine).


Regards
-- =


