@NODE "Mail_671" "Re: Grand Theft AMiGA"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 25 Mar 1999 14:56:42 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 25 Mar 99 13:52:31 +0000
Subject: Re: Grand Theft AMiGA
Encoding: 7bit

> Well, you could just have multiple look-up tables. I dunno realy. I still go for pre-rendered.

you dont really need lookup tables to do rotation. a realtime rotation
would be the same quality as you could do in most graphics software.
the only benefit of prerendering is that if you were making the cars
in a raytracer you could render at a particular angle to get better
antialiasing and so on. There certainly aint no point in
texturemapping the cars if you only ever see them from the same
position.

-- 
Paul.

