@NODE "Mail_717" "Re: Grand Theft AMiGA"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 1 Apr 1999 13:02:32 +0100
From: Centro Amiga <centro.amiga@ip.pt>
Date: Thu, 01 Apr 1999 12:52:52 +0000
Organization: Centro Amiga
Subject: Re: Grand Theft AMiGA

Hya Mikkel

> Since when has realtime calculations been faster than lookup tables ?

Ever since processor speed became faster than memory access.
Nowadays, most processors can actually do many calculations in less
time than what they would need to fetch a value from a LUT in memory.
LUT`s are 80`s style programming, not 90`s or 00`s. Of course this is based
on simple calcs, not complex ones. If you have a complex op. that takes
say 2+  simple ops. it may be faster to use LUT`s. The only sure way is to
do
the tests :-))

Cya

Silver
aka Nuno Trancoso


