@NODE "Mail_718" "Re: Grand Theft AMiGA"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 1 Apr 1999 14:46:58 +0100
Date: Thu, 01 Apr 1999 13:56:00 +0100
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Subject: Re: Grand Theft AMiGA
encoding: 7bit
X-Accept-Language: en

Centro Amiga wrote:
> > Since when has realtime calculations been faster than lookup tables ?
> 
> Ever since processor speed became faster than memory access.
> Nowadays, most processors can actually do many calculations in less
> time than what they would need to fetch a value from a LUT in memory.
> LUT`s are 80`s style programming, not 90`s or 00`s. Of course this is based
> on simple calcs, not complex ones.

Yeah, don`t nock the old Look Up Tables too much. They're usefull for
storing information that can take a LOT of calculating. I use LUT's a
great deal this week to add Gouraud shaded texturemapping with dithered
texture blending to Foundation. There was no way I'd ever manage to get
that effect with real-time but with a few smart lookup tables and a few
other tricks I managed to impliment it with the same cpu power as
the old pre-rendered chunky shapes so it didn`t even raise the cpu
requirements as I'd previously expected. The memory taken up by the look
up tables was only half the size of my old pre-rendered shapes! So
I didn`t even have to worry about wasting memory which is very easy to
do when you get greedy with your LUT's :)

Anyway, I have to finish of the update and get it released by the end
of today. A lot of people thought it was an April Fools joke! :) Take
a look at http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk/FoundSupport.html before
the end of Thursday to see why it looks like an April fool.

Cheers,

Paul



-- 
< Paul Burkey http://www.sneech.freeserve.co.uk >


