@NODE "Mail_728" "GFX Card Friendly"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 13 Mar 1999 22:16:21 +0000
From: Anthony Sherratt <shezzor@asp.u-net.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Mar 1999 21:33:19 +0000
Organization: ASP/Warrington
Subject: GFX Card Friendly

Hello,

I know GFX Cards have been the in thing lately :)  but seeing as I dont
have one (yet) its going to be hard to program for one.  Now this is
my point to this email, If I use Mildred for example for a chunky 
display does that instantly make my program GFX card friendly ?  

If not could you please explain in more detail what I need to do or 
what commands I need to step-toe around, please ?

I've learnt so much about the AMiGA being on this list its 
unbelivable, so dont fail me now :)

Regards

Anthony Sherratt
-- 
<sb> *ASP Software* 
<sb> (http://www.asp.u-net.com)
<sb> *Last Updated: 17th Feb 1999*
<sb> ICQ Num : 16295659   
<tsb>
<sb> *CURRENT GAMES IN DEVELOPMENT*
<sb> Survivors DX - [################=--]85%
<sb> Conquest - [#=-----------------]10% 
<tsb>
REAL PROGRAMMERS make sure that if they're using line numbers, they
never use the same numeric increment twice. (Eg: 10, 11, 13, 1004..)




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_729" "Re: GFX Card Friendly"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 13 Mar 1999 22:43:23 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 13 Mar 99 22:42:17 +0000
Subject: Re: GFX Card Friendly
Encoding: 7bit

> I know GFX Cards have been the in thing lately :)  but seeing as I dont
> have one (yet) its going to be hard to program for one.  Now this is
> my point to this email, If I use Mildred for example for a chunky 
> display does that instantly make my program GFX card friendly ?  

Almost.

The only part left to do in non-mildred code (although it may in some
way use some mildred commands) is the actual output to a display,
which you need to use something like writepixelarray8 for. See the
screen2.lha demo at http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk

> If not could you please explain in more detail what I need to do or 
> what commands I need to step-toe around, please ?

Well mildred will handle the blitting and manipulation of your chunky
data but you have to get your data from chunky to the display. Either
you can set up a c2pWindow object and use Mc2p to convert it to a
planar AGA display, or some rtg output method.
 
> I've learnt so much about the AMiGA being on this list its 
> unbelivable, so dont fail me now :)

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk



@ENDNODE
