> I put it in my CD, click the Install and away we go!
> 
> Somewhere in the installing it fails.  Script failuer or something.
> 
> I tried several times to install it, but it always fails when at the same
> part of the script.
> 
> That's it!  When extracting an archive.  Same one every time.

Think I had the same problem with the Ultimate Blitz CD. If I 
remember correctly I ran the installer with Snoopdos and examined the 
install script  and discovered the installer was expecting one of the 
directories on the CD to be in RAM: and it wasn't. I copied that 
directory to RAM: and ran the installer again and it worked.

To get the online help working you have to manually set the 's' bit 
on one of the files too - can't remember which but snoopdos should 
show that one up too.

Hope this helps.

Mike Child


