@NODE "Mail_747" "Re: ForcePal (Re: My Stupid Game!)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 25 Mar 1999 00:25:55 +0000
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Mar 1999 18:19:40 -0500
Subject: Re: ForcePal (Re: My Stupid Game!)

Hi amorel

On 23-Mar-99, amorel wrote:
> On 23-Mar-99, Curt Esser wrote:
> 
> C=The only drawback is that ForcePAL causes an Enforcer hit  (not raelly
> C=harmful, it's a "Read" from somewhere it shouldn't be reading).
> 
> Thats what blitz`s aslfilerequest command does, 2 read hits. It isnt a big
> deal if it does that?

Well, in theory NOTHING should ever cause an enforcer hit.  But I've never
found a "read" hit to cause any real problems  (assuming the program in
question doesn't crash at that point!)  It's just "looking" at an area of
memory that the program doesn't own.

The "write" hits are what cause the real problems.

But I'm surprised that the ASLFileRequest command would cause a hit.  I
never had a problem with it here.  Are you MAXLEN'ing the path and file
name strings first?
And have the debugger turned off?   The debugger causes many enforcer
hits... 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




