@NODE "Mail_765" "Re: ForcePal (Re: My Stupid Game!)"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 27 Mar 1999 09:14:36 +0000
From: Damir Arh <damir.arh@guest.arnes.si>
Date: Sat, 27 Mar 1999 10:08:17 +0100
Subject: Re: ForcePal (Re: My Stupid Game!)

Hello Curt

On 26-Mar-99, you typed in:

> On 25-Mar-99, stocksjames wrote:

>> Right.. ...erm.. ..what's MMU?
 
> It's a Memory Management Unit.  Correct me if I'm wrong, but I think you
> have one if you've got an 030 or better, and don't have one with 020 or
> 000.
 
> It, ahhh..  Manages your Memory, I suppose?  (OK, I have no idea...)
 
> I think it allows you to have soft-kicked "ROMS" and stuff like that...

Well MMU takes care of the Virtual Memory and stuff. It translates virtual
addresses to hardware ones and things like that. As virtual memory is
always software driven, it allows software checks of the addresses the
computer reads/writes, which makes it possible for programs like Enforcer
to work. (according to my computer architecture lecturer)


Kind regards from Slovenia
