hiya.

I need to do some conversions of .quick values into .float values,
eventually in asm. Although the .q can be considered a longword, you
can't just use something like SPFlt_ because it only converts an
integer to a floating point and i need to retain the fractional part
of the .quick value.

Eventually I need to call Cos and Sin routines from within asm. Any
suggestions as to how? I figure I can use mathffp.library but firstly
i have to convert my quicks into the proper format. I'm not sure of
the difference between the IEEE commands such as IEEESPFlt and the
non-ieee ones.

I basically need to be able to take some quick values, treat them as
longwords in order to do some multiplications, then somehow find a
cosine and sine of those values, and finally convert back to a quick
so that a final multiplication can be done. Any suggestions as to how
to do this would be appreciated. Also does anyone know if blitz's .f
float variable type is the same as that used by the mathffp lib, and
if so, could it be used instead (bearing in mind i dont wanna have to
do too many floating point multiplies and such). ?

