> 2, does anyone know how to find out if a specific WB pen is in use? And =
if
>    not change it and lock it?

That'll be ObtainPen_ you want. You can specify what pen you want, new RGB=
 
values and there's a flag to say whether to change to these new RGB values=
 or 
not. See the graphics.library autodoc.

> 3, Also dont y`all think the #Scroll# command is hellishly slow?, cuts t=
he

 Yes. If you can, use BlockScroll. It uses 16 pixel wide blocks, so that t=
he 
blitter can work properly, don't know if the target needs to be aligned to=
 16 
though (probably does).

 There's also bound to be a CPUScroll command or funtion somewhere. Maybe =
as 
part of Dave Newton's CPU gfx stuff.


