Subject: Re: Emulating window functions & WB Pens & Scrolling
Date: Tue, 30 Mar 1999 16:20:56 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit



>> [=> There's also bound to be a CPUScroll command or funtion somewhere.
[=>
>> Maybe as part of Dave Newton's CPU gfx stuff.
>>
>> Do you know the filename? I just been hunting for it on AmiNet, and
>> downloaded half the stuff on there I didn`t have :),.. But still couldn`t
>> find it :(
>
>I think the archive is on Rui's site.


I think there`s a block scroll...not sure really....I haven`t released a
version for some time, and the new version will have scroll....and other
things, like fonts, blit effects etc. The thing you should do is use cpu
blit, and do all your graphics work in fastram, and then scroll from a
fastram bitmap to your display bitmap....you would gain quite a bit of time
to do all your graphics. (the best thing, if your using the display lib
would be to allocate a bitmap with 16 pixels extra width, and do a larger
but faster block scroll, then do the fine scroll with the display hardware)


If you need a copy..let me know...I never got around to putting it on
aminet..because it wasn`t really mean`t to be a release version...and the
next one isn`t really complete yet! (hopefully in a week I`ll have it about
ready)

Dave



