@NODE "Mail_793" "Re: Drawing on Fast Ram Bitmaps"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 2 Mar 1999 01:50:19 +0000
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Tue, 2 Mar 1999 01:49:33 +0000
Date: Tue, 02 Mar 1999 01:26:48 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Drawing on Fast Ram Bitmaps
Encoding: 7bit

Anthony Sherratt wrote:
> Is there anyway you can draw on fastram bitmaps using
> the normal drawing routines or even the NCS drawing
> routines ?

Most "Normal" drawing commands will use direct blitter control or
OS functions which also use the blitter for many drawing jobs. I've
not used NCS but I think they`re just like the "normal" blitz
graphics functions except better (they use the OS for everything).
The blitter can`t work in fast ram so it would probably just.
 
> Everytime I try to do so, the graphics seem to get corrupted.

Yep, thats is.

Cheers,

Paul

