@NODE "Mail_794" "DLL is here!!"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 31 Mar 1999 01:16:54 +0100
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: DLL is here!!
Date: Wed, 31 Mar 1999 01:17:09 +0100
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_0006_01BE7B14.3533C460"

------=_NextPart_000_0006_01BE7B14.3533C460
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

Hi all,

 Well, I finally finished my dynamic linked list routines...hope it`s useful
to someone :)...

 Just a few things....if any one wants to do some examples that would be
appreciated...

 I have tested it...but it`s bound to have bugs in it....so let me know if
you know 4 sure there is a bug in my routines..

 Could someone test listview compatability...I think it should work..see the
doc enclosed

 There is a sort included, a slow one in the main include file, and a fast
one in a seperate include. The faster one requires extra memory and stack
space....I haven`t tested it to see how much stack space it`s using...so if
someone could look into that...it`d be handy to have some minimum and
maximum values..

The string sort is case insensetive (ie, treats PaRt as part)

 It`d be cool to turn it into a library...but I haven`t got the time...if
someone else could do it, I could help if you get stuck....(probably quite
easy as I don`t call a lot of blitz routines).

 I`ve had to included a few small blitz replacement routines (ie, I
sometimes get funny peek values and other blitz bugs)....did you know that
sgn() can`t tell if a float is negative?? (very useful!)

Any other useful functions needed??


Just test test test and let me know what happens please....

Dave


------=_NextPart_000_0006_01BE7B14.3533C460
