@NODE "Mail_799" "Re: Display Alignment problems"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 23 Mar 1999 10:42:59 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 23 Mar 99 10:41:39 +0000
Subject: Re: Display Alignment problems
Encoding: 7bit

> I've been programming using Mildred 1.35, and I decided to upgrade to v1.46.
>  After doing so, my program is now displayed 16pixels to the left.  This is
> also happening when I run mscreen and mscreen2.  Any ideas on how I can
> make sure the display is set correctly?   I had this problem with an
> earlier version of Mildred, but v1.35 seemed to fixed it.  Is this an old
> bug come back to life?

In version 1.45 some modifications were made to the cludge commans,
such as MCludgeBitmap. It used to be necessary, when passing the base
address of the memory to be cludged, to subtract 16 from that address
so that the cludge would end up pointing to the correct location. In
1.45 this was taken out of the programmers hands and implemented
internally. So, on the lines where you've used MCludgeBitmap,
MCludgeShape, etc, you will need to remove the `-16' from the end of
the line I expect.

Incidentally, you should find updated versions of MScreen and MScreen2
on the website with support for v1.45 so that the cludging is done
properly.

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk



@ENDNODE
