@NODE "Mail_806" "Devices"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 2 Mar 1999 10:26:51 +0000
 id 10HmCh-0005ja-00; Tue, 2 Mar 1999 10:15:07 +0000
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Tue, 02 Mar 1999 10:15:07 +0000
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
Subject: Devices
Encoding: 7bit

Hello!

I needed some cd commands for a game I'm doing but the RICompactDiskLib
seemed a bit buggy which led on to me trying to use cd.device directly
(eventually i'll use squirrelscsi.device but that can wait) which
brought me onto the problem of using devices.  I've opened the device
and got back the IORequest structure but to use the cd.device commands I
need a IOStdReq.  This has the same fields as IORequest so surely I can
interchange them?  Anyway my code currently looks like this and causes a
rather nice IOError guru.

#CD_EJECT = 23
If OpenDevice_("cd.device",2,*IOR.IOStdReq,0)=0
  *IOR\io_Command = #CD_EJECT
  *IOR\io_Data    = 0
  *IOR\io_Length  = 1
  *IOR\io_Offset  = 0
  CheckMe=DoIO_(*IOR)
  CloseDevice_(*IOR)
EndIf
End


Any help gratefully accepted

    Thom



@ENDNODE
