@NODE "Mail_808" "Re: Devices"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 8 Mar 1999 10:45:55 +0000
 id 10JxWn-0002ZE-00; Mon, 8 Mar 1999 10:44:53 +0000
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Mon, 08 Mar 1999 10:44:53 +0000
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: Devices
Encoding: 7bit

Hi!

After much crashing I finally sorted out using devices... Here's a small
example which ejects a cd using cd.device.  Some of you might find it
useful.

*myport.MsgPort = CreateMsgPort_  ;Set up msg port
If *myport                        ;for device to reply to

  *IOReq.IOStdReq = CreateIORequest_(*myport,100)

                                  ;Create IORequest with 100
                                  ;bytes space (actually an
                                  ;IOStdReq to give extra
                                  ;fields for device commands

  If OpenDevice_("cd.device",0,*IOReq.IOStdReq,0)=0

    *IOReq\io_Command = 23      ;Equivalent to CD_EJECT
    *IOReq\io_Data = 0          ;Null
    *IOReq\io_Length = 1        ;Eject CD (0 is insert)
    *IOReq\io_Offset = 0
    error = DoIO_(*IOReq) = 0   ;Send command to device
    CloseDevice_ *IOReq
  EndIf
  DeleteIORequest_ *IOReq       ;Clean up
  DeleteMsgPort_ *myport
EndIf
End

    Thom



@ENDNODE
