@NODE "Mail_831" "Re: Cursor position in GTString gadgets"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 10 Mar 1999 21:31:09 +0000
From: "Scott" <scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Cursor position in GTString gadgets
Date: Wed, 10 Mar 1999 21:28:46 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

On the 9th March 1999, Krzysztof Jonko asked:


>If anbody know which tags I shoud use to set cursor position in GTString
>gadget? Initial string is for example:"abcdef" - when I activate String
>gadget cursor is under letter "a" but I want to set cursor position AFTER
>last char of initial strings. Any ideas?

An Idea:

Don't create your GTString gadget with an initial string, but instead do this:

ActivateString win,gad
Type "InitialString"

(Type being the blitz command of course, I'm not suggesting you just type
it in. That would be silly)

Your GTString gadget will now have "InitialString" in it, with the cursor
positioned at the end.

Not pretty, not elegant, but effective.


Regards,
Scott

scott@assembler.free-online.co.uk



Damn the prime directive, give the Borg Windows 3.1   -   Lt. Worf




@ENDNODE
