> Dont bullshit too much about it or you might become embarassed ;-)

> I`m sorry to say, but imho any copy protection is a waste of time. It`l=
l
> always be cracked, always, always and always. If not than its not worth=
it
> as noone buys it.

Ah, but here's the deal. Copy protections aren't done so it's impossible =
to copy something, it's done to "buy some time". You see the longer it ta=
kes to crack something (obviously we'e not talking the AMiGA market here)=
 the longer it will be "unavailable" and you'll have to go and buy the or=
iginal to play it. In average a very high level of copy protection (Like =
Commando(e)s and Thief) will buy EIDOS at least three months of extra sal=
es (Which is several million pounds) where as a low level of copy protect=
ion (Uneal) won't. So anyone who takes themselves seiously will add some =
high level copy potection, because while it won't deter those hell bent o=
n cacking it, it will certainly incease sales on a large scale.


Regards
-- =

