I think the demo is called Bounce9.lha at
http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk

also Remap.lha.

They have source in there as example of how to generate the lookup
tables needed.

Yes lights are similar to just a remap. You can either have one level
of light change, for which you can use MSimpleReMapMode, or if you
want various levels of intensity/transparency then you should use
MReMapMode to combine the shape with the destination. It's then just a
matter of computing the lookup table to give the desired effect.

Incidentally, what type of game engine is it that is flying along so
nicely?

-- 
Paul.

