Errr, yes.  At least in the case of my sources  ("mess" being the operative
word)

What it actually does is make up an executable program, including all the
Blitz libraries you have used commands from  (these are really a collection
of machine code routines) and the code that calls these routines, and feeds
them parameters, as necessary.

