Hello,

  Ok,... Problems again :) <GRiN>

Now, I`m new to all this ARexx stuff, but even I can tell that when you have
a  command setup called "IEREQUEST" (And it does work and accept it),..
and a script calls it like so:

IEREQUEST '"Request"' '"Do you have a pet?"' '"Dog|Cat|Fish"'

That #RXGetArg#(1) should not take this as:

"IEREQUEST Request Do you have a pet? Dog|Cat|Fish"

Should it?

Shouldn`t #RXGetArg#(1)="Request"
          #RXGetArg#(2)="Do you have a pet?"
          #RXGetArg#(3)="Dog|Cat|Fish"
????

I`m using (at the moment) a section from the example to parse the arguments:

  ArgC.w=0
  RXNA=#RXNumArgs#
  #For# RXA=1 To RXNA
    #InitArgParse# #RXGetArg#(RXA)
    #For# TMP=0 To 15
      Arg$(ArgC)=#NextArg$#
      ArgC+1
    #Next# TMP
  #Next# RXA

Erm, and from what I can tell, the above should work...

Can anyone help please?
Haven`t got a clue what I`m going to do next if there is no solution to
this.

BTW - The rexx example cocks up too when it comes to the REQUEST command.

Ta

Cya!
