@NODE "Mail_932" "Blitz Serial, and the 060"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Mon, 8 Mar 1999 06:56:30 +0000
Date: 08 Mar 99 17:54:11 +1000
From: "David Fong" <vkelim@netspace.net.au>
Subject: Blitz Serial, and the 060
encoding: 7bit

Hello all!

Is anyone else having trouble with Blitz serial routines
and the 060 (or the 040 for that matter)?

When I wrote my Amiga Newton Package installer, various people
with 060s (and 040s I think) complained my program did not work,
with many errors occurring during communication.  I had a 030
at that stage and could not figure out what the problem was.

Well, now I have a 060, and I am experiencing the problems
they report!  I cannot figure out what is going wrong, but
I think the Blitz serial routines are to blame.

Turning off superscalar and branch cache (cpu060 nb ns) helps,
but not completely.  Especially when I am trying to transfer
250Kb packages...

I notice that `RI' has released a fast serial library (according
to the allocated serial library numbersrs), perhaps that will help?

Where can I get that library?

Cheerio, David.

David P.S. Fong - Traralgon, 3844, Australia.
Dr.David.Fong@medical.net.au - Surfing and working - Amiga 1200 and Newton
http://www.users.bigpond.com/vkelim/ - PGP public key available



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_933" "Re: Blitz Serial, and the 060"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Tue, 9 Mar 1999 12:13:01 +0000
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Tue, 9 Mar 1999 12:12:14 +0000
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 08 Mar 1999 14:52:36 +0000
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: Blitz Serial, and the 060

On 08-Mar-99, David Fong wrote:

> Is anyone else having trouble with Blitz serial routines
> and the 060 (or the 040 for that matter)?

> When I wrote my Amiga Newton Package installer, various people
> with 060s (and 040s I think) complained my program did not work,
> with many errors occurring during communication.  I had a 030
> at that stage and could not figure out what the problem was.

> Well, now I have a 060, and I am experiencing the problems
> they report!  I cannot figure out what is going wrong, but
> I think the Blitz serial routines are to blame.

Are you by any chance using the interrupts to notify your program when
their's stuff waiting to be collected on the serial port? If you are, then
that's probably your bug.  I can't get them to work at all on my 040, but
they used to work when I just had an 020.

> I notice that `RI' has released a fast serial library (according
> to the allocated serial library numbersrs), perhaps that will help?

> Where can I get that library?

It's packaged as part of the Blitz Support Suite

-- 
