@NODE "Mail_937" "Blitz Library( asm )"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 6 Mar 1999 04:38:04 +0000
From: Roger Beausoleil <vision_fx@citenet.net>
Date: Fri, 05 Mar 1999 21:57:25 -0500
Subject: Blitz Library( asm )

Hi all,

I wrote two commands to create a PopUpMenuGadget( Mix Between Cycle & List) in
Blitz... I would like to converts them in ONE command in a new library. My
problem is,... I have 9 arguments in total... and my knowledge in ASM is
limited... 

How can I get arguments from the stack, if I need 9 args in the command?
Ex:  !afunction{ #long }
     !args{ #long,#word,#word,#word,#word,#word,#string,#long,#long }
             d0    d1    d2      d3    d4     d5     d6    d7( I do not know
if I can use d7 )
     How I get args after d6 or d7?

Any help will be very appreciate!
Roger





@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_938" "Re: Blitz Library( asm )"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Thu, 25 Mar 1999 14:11:37 +0000
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <flameduck@software.dk>
Date: Thu, 25 Mar 1999 12:02:04 +0200
Organization: M2 productions
Subject: Re: Blitz Library( asm )
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Roger.

On 06-Mar-99, Roger Beausoleil wrote:

> How can I get arguments from the stack, if I need 9 args in the command=
?
> Ex:  !afunction{ #long }
>     !args{ #long,#word,#word,#word,#word,#word,#string,#long,#long }
>             d0    d1    d2      d3    d4     d5     d6    d7( I do not =
know
> if I can use d7 )
>     How I get args after d6 or d7?

I don't know aboout Blitz, but I don't see any problem using d7. Also, yo=
u can use Address registers, a0-a6. (a7 being the stack pointer, it's not=
 wise to change it). Also, for Blitz a5 is the gobal varibale pointer or =
something, so don't mess arround with that either, unless you restore it =
afterwards. I guess that's it really....




Regards
-- =


