@NODE "Mail_941" "Re: Blitz AREXX question."
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sun, 14 Mar 1999 10:07:10 +0000
From: "Richard Brooklyn" <richbrooklyn@free4all.co.uk>
Organization: Brooklyn Towers
Date: 14 Mar 99 08:53:09 +0000
Subject: Re: Blitz AREXX question.
Encoding: 7bit

> Hello,
> 
>     What does the user have to have RexxMast running for exactly?
> What I mean is: Do they only need it to execute scripts?
> Will #RXCreatePort# fail if they dont have it running?
> What does RexxMast do exactly? I dont think it handles opening or
> RexxPorts does it?
> 
Think of it this way, if you want to send an E-Mail you'll need an
E-Mail program, If you want to look at web sites you'll need a web
browser and to run AREXX scripts you'll need to have RexxMast 
running, it's as simple as that relly.

Rexxmast only came on Workbench 2.04 or over. RexxMast dosen't take up
much memory and ticks over in the background You should copy it over
to WBStartup and forget about it. 

I can't help you with the blitz side of things as I never use blitz to
use AREXX. AREXX is very easy to learn, if you can use blitz or write
AmigaDOS scripts you'll pick it up in no time.

You should buy the next issue of Amiga Format (comes out on monday in
