@NODE "Mail_956" "Re: Animation Format's"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Wed, 31 Mar 1999 12:00:50 +0100
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 31 Mar 99 11:50:06 +0000
Subject: Re: Animation Format's
Encoding: 7bit

> > Any ideas? I need an animation format that supports sound...thanks
> 
> It aint the best solution but a solution is CDXL, I think it's pretty good,
> albeit, somewhat outdated and not overly compressed....

Hmm,  it seems that quite a lot of people are wanting to get
animations and possibly also sound into their games these days, and
yet there is no really suitable format. Particularly people are
needing more and more to run anims in chunky and although there are
thigs like avi, mpeg, cdxl etc, we all know full well that these don't
have very good quality and require lots of cpu time. Ok so yes you
wont get 24bit frames and 16bit sound from a 2xspeed cdrom at 25fps
but I dont think there is actually a decent 256-colour format. The
anim 5-8 format is somewhat slow when played in chunky as it is
designed for a planar output. Perhaps we should get together and
design a new format for our games?

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
