@NODE "Mail_970" "Advantages and Disadvantages, PLEASE READ ME"
 for scott@online.u-net.com; Sat, 6 Mar 1999 13:50:44 +0000
 ([62.136.94.237] helo=194.152.64.35 ident=NCPIPLCP)
	by mail12.svr.pol.co.uk with smtp (Exim 2.12 #1)
	id 10JHSn-0000hj-00
	for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sat, 6 Mar 1999 13:49:58 +0000
From: Loki <loki@napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 06 Mar 1999 13:52:14 +0100
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Advantages and Disadvantages, PLEASE READ ME

Hello Cool Blitzy type people :),

*#ORIGINAL BLITZ LIST:#*

  /ADVANTAGES:/

 o It is `THE BLITZ LIST' and everyone knows it as such.
 o EVERYONE is already on this list!

  /DISADVANTAGES:/

 o Has no adminstration WHAT SO EVER!
 o Is old and slow (Yes it is! try posting a multirecipient mail to both
    lists and see which you get back first! :))
 o Has no moderation, and is setup to allow mail from people who are not
    subscribed. And noone can change this! :(
 o Nodody has any control at all over it! :)
 o Is bloody hard and annoying to subscribe and unsubscribe, we have
    learnt that by the amount of people post mail to the list asking
    how to unsubscribe,. and people getting angry when they cant :)
 o We still have that mail bouncing off Andrew Drays closed account :(

*#NEW BLITZ LIST:#*

  /ADVANTAGES:/

 o Can be COMPLETELY moderated to suit the group!
 o Is fast and effiecient.
 o Mail can be posted to the list from the Web.
 o All mail sent is kept at egroups. Ready to read whenever you want to,
    so you dont have to keep all that blitz mail and worry you deleted 
    something you might need later!
 o Mail can be read on the web (so not as much need for the aminet postings.)
 o Is very easy to subscribe and unsubscribe an email address to the list!
    No messing about, no fuss!
 o Each individual person can change the way they are subscribed to the
    list, set their own personal settings to differnt types of subscription,
    like: Web-Base mail/Account EMail.
 o PROPER polls can be created!
 o REAL SPAM mail is instatly detected by EGroups! (Oh yes it is :) )
 o Can subscribe and unsubscribe from the web-site.
 o Can have the subscribe-box HTML on your own site. And people can sign
    up from there.
 o Statistics are automatically recorded for the list! And can be read
    online.
 o Most of all, there is a point of inquiry when something goes horribly
    wrong, or you need help :)

  /DISADVANTAGES:/

 o SPAM messages at the bottom of every mail posted (which can be removed
    if we pay the $5 (which I dont think is too much to ask?))
 o It is not as widely known as the original,.. and will need a lot of work
    to get it up to scratch. 
 o Could be very hard to get people to move (the stubern ones :) eheheh)

*#SOLUTIONS:#*

 1, Everone stay where they are (on the old blitz-list).
 2, Everyone move over to the new blitz-list (Blitz-List 2000?) and we 
    appoint someone to post a regular mail to the old blitz list to
    inform people who have subscribed that the blitz-list has moved
    and give them all the details for subscribing to the new one :)


So,.. which is best solution?
Remember it only take 2 emails to get you off the old list and on the new
one!

Cya!
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>*CONTACTING ME:*
<sb>E-MAIL: loki@napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk | ICQ: 27181384
<sb>WWW: http://www.napalmdeath.freeserve.co.uk/
<tsb>
<sb>CURRENT PROJECT: IconExtreme V3.01 [...:......] 40% Complete!
<tsb>
