Ahahaha :) Ok, cos it`s the blitz list,... I`ll give you a more realistic
rundown :)........

o Send message to EZELM
o Wait a min or so
o Get error back
o Try again
o Get another error back
o Write message to the list, asking for help
o Wait 5 hours
o Read response from David McMinn or Mikkel :)
o Attempt alternative unsubscription method
o Wait a min or so
o Get success message back
-
o Write message to blitz-list-subscribe@egroups.com
o Wait 5 seconds :) lol
o Get Warning (So email cant be faked in your name)
o Reply to it
o Wait 5 seconds again
o Get welcome message :)

I`m biased :) I`ll shut up now, and let y`all make up your own minds..
But having managed egroups before, I know the pros and cons, really,
EGroups is better, trust me :)

